Commentary.Commentary: The players are back out in the middle. Shan Masood and Imam-ul-Haq are the openers for Pakistan. The question now is - Will the strawberry swing? Mitchell Starc will try and be the first person to answer. Masood to face.

So with a humongous score of 589, Pakistan will need to fight out of their skins to even save this Test. The onus will be on the openers to provide them with a good start as the sun is setting down. Australia will look to grab a couple of scalps before the final session. What will happen? Join us in a while for Pakistan's first innings.

A forgetful performance by the visitors. Barring Shaheen Afridi no one showed much of a fight with the pink ball. They managed to get only three wickets and all of them went to the left-arm pacer. Musa Khan would like to erase this debut from his memory. Yasir Shah had a dreadful game as well. Abbas had a nightmare return. Well, when a team scores 589 and manages to lose just 3 wickets, then it is pretty evident that the bowlers have had a horror show.

What a batting masterclass from David Warner. A knock to cherish for him. His massive, massive score of 335 along with 162 from Marnus Labuschagne has seen Australia declare for a humongous score of 589/3. Steven Smith and Matthew Wade played good supporting roles helping Warner make the second highest run scorer for Australia in an innings.
That will be the declaration. David Warner walks off to a standing ovation from the crowd. His teammates are standing around the ropes giving him an ovation as well.

So - what is the topic of discussion? Of course - the 400 by Brian Lara. But spare a thought for Sir Don Bradman. Remember Mark Taylor's innings when he declared and same for Michael Clarke? Both felt that the Don's score should not be surpassed. Don't think Warner has any such intention to stop at this juncture. Michael Hussey raises a good point on air though. Should Australia wait for Warner to get to his 400? There is really bad weather forecast for Day 3 but Michael Vaughan believes that Australia's bowling attack is so good that they can take 10 wickets twice on this pitch, in 2 days.

FOUR! Yes! Yes! Yes! TRIPLE HUNDRED FOR DAVID WARNER! Wow! This is  one of the best knocks you will ever see. He has played superbly in this innings. He is pumped up and its his moment to cherish. He  sprints, jumps and pumps the air for the umpteenth time in this game. He removes his helmet and raises his bat with a huge smile on his face. The whole of Adelaide crowd is on its feet to applaud the knock of the genius. He bows down like an artist and soaks in all the applause. Warner then once again looks at the heavens remembering his friend and former teammate Phil Hughes. Back of a length ball around off, Warner pulls it to get to his maiden Test triple ton. It feels like a special day for David. Is Warner going to break Lara's record of 400?

NOT OUT! Poor review from Pakistan and they have lost both their reviews. Good length ball around off, Wade looks to defend but it goes off something to the keeper. Shaheen Afridi is on his bike as he starts celebrating. The others appeal but the umpire is unmoved. They have a chat about it and decide to take it  upstairs. Replay rolls in and Hot Spot shows no mark as the ball goes past the bat. The sound was of the ball hitting the pad.

Pakistan feel there is a thin outside edge but the umpire has disagreed. After a chat the tourists have decided to use their second review. It looks like there is nothing off the bat. The Hot Spot rolls in and it shows there is nothing.

Third wicket for Shaheen Afridi. He has been the only shining spot in this bowling unit. Maybe Australia are looking to declare sooner rather than later and are looking for quick runs maybe that's why the shot.

We are back for the second session. The Pakistan players are out in the middle. David Warner and Steven Smith will resume their innings for the hosts. Yasir Shah will start the proceedings for the second session.
... Day 2, Session 2 ...

It was another timid performance by the visitors with the strawberry. Once again apart from Shaheen Afridi none of them looked quite threatening. Muhammad Musa's debut has been a forgetful one so far as he almost had sent Warner packing but he overstepped his line. Yasir Shah too has had a torrid time going for over 6 rpo and being wicketless. The body language of the hosts has been very poor and by the looks of it it looks like they have already surrendered. Overall it was a scrappy performance by the tourists. Will Australia's onslaught continue or will Pakistan show some fight? Join us after the break to find out.

What a brilliant session for the hosts. They have made a mind-boggling 173 runs in this session and have lost just a solitary wicket. Labuschagne and Warner continued from where they left off on Day 1. Labuschagne got to his 150 but departed early on as the second new ball was taken. Smith then joined Warner and made it feel like he was batting for a long time as well as he went about his business. David Warner got to his 200 and then rode some luck to get to his 250 before coming out unscathed to Tea with an unbeaten 261. The pair of Smith and Warner have added 106 taking Australia in a commanding position.

On being asked about his innings so far, Warner smiles and says that he has had some luck. Tells he is looking to play with discipline and has tried to maintain that. On his celebration on reaching 200, Warner says that one does not always achieve that feat and he is happy to have helped his team.
Warner walks out with a huge smile on his face. And the man of the moment is caught down for a quick chat.

Marnus Labuschagne is giving an interview on the sides. Labuschagne says that they have a great start on the home soil and in this game. Marnus says cricket is a funny game as you score 162 but still walk off disappointed. On Warner's batting says that there is a great intensity and they enjoy batting with each other as they are similar players. Adds it was good to make a big partnership. Says that he has made some technical changes and he just looks to stay in the moment and stay focused rather than getting ahead of himself. Further adds that he looks to learn from the likes of Smith and Warner and grasp in as much as he can.

Once again Musa has overstepped his line. A tough lesson for the youngster and he has learnt it the hard way.

On a good length on off, David looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
FOUR! Terrific shot. Length delivery on off, Warner drives it beautifully through covers for a boundary.
On a good length on off, Warner plays it to point.
Outside off, David leaves it alone.
Good length delivery outside off, Warner offers no shot to this one.

There it is! There it is! 200 for David Warner! Take a bow! This has been one of his best knocks. Good length ball around the pads, Warner glances it behind square on the leg side and gets to the other end. He removes his helmet, continues his run and pumps the air in joy in trademark Warner fashion. The crowd applauds his knock. David kisses his helmet and looks at the sky paying tribute to his former teammate, Phil Hughes. An emotional sight to see. Terrific from David Warner!
Good length ball on off, Warner defends it and makes everyone wait for his double ton just like he did before his century.
Moves to 199! Fuller on the pads, Warner flicks it through mid-wicket for a couple.
Smith is off the mark! Good length ball on off, Steven strokes it towards mid on for a single.
Out walks Steven Smith at number 4!

OUT! BOWLED! Finally, finally, Pakistan have something to cheer about! Excellent bowling from Shaheen Afridi. He has been the best bowler for Pakistan and just like on Day 1 he has a wicket with the new ball. The second new ball this time. A lapse of concentration maybe from Labuschagne. Fuller around off, Marnus looks to drive it straight leaving a big gap between his bat and pad. The ball jags back in and goes right through the gate to uproot the off pole. End of a superb knock from Marnus Labuschagne. He will be gutted to miss out on a double ton but boy has this not been a gem of an innings to watch!  He walks off to a standing ovation from the crowd and he deserves every bit of it. The gigantic partnership of 361 has finally come to an end.
Outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms to this one.
Shaheen Afridi, the best bowler for Pakistan in this Test is on for the first time today.
Length delivery outside off, Warner punches it through covers. The batsmen get two runs.
Outside off, Warner lets it go.
Good length delivery on off, Warner defends it off the front foot.
Third consecutive leave for David Warner. Outside off again, Warner leaves it alone.
Outside off, Warner shoulders arms to this one.
On a good length and outside off, Warner offers no shot to this one.
Second new ball has been taken. Will the change of ball bring in a change of fortune for the visitors?
Floated delivery on off, Labuschagne drives it to covers.
Flighted delivery outside off, Marnus looks to cut but misses it.

FOUR! Almost an action replay of the previous shot. Short around off, Marnus cuts this one again through point. The only difference this time is Imam-ul-Haq at deep point dives and tries to save the boundary  but misses.
FOUR! Short and wide outside off, Labuschagne gets on his back foot and cuts it through point for a boundary.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Warner flicks it towards mid-wicket for a run.
Flighted delivery on middle, Labuschagne flicks it towards square leg. The batsmen take a single.
On a length on middle, Warner nudges it to the leg side.
Length delivery on middle, Labuschagne flicks it towards mid-wicket. The batsmen take a single.

Marnus Labuschagne pulls out of his stance in the last moment. The ball had missed the stumps so no issue. Would have been very interesting to see had the ball hit the stumps. Because Marnus was extremely late to get out of the way. Though he kept saying sorry a couple of times.
On a length on off, Labuschagne plays it to covers.
Length delivery outside off, Labuschagne drives it through covers. The batsmen pick up a couple.
Good length delivery on off, Marnus keeps it out.
On a good length on off, Labuschagne punches it to point.
Mohammad Abbas is back on. 19-6-56-0 are his figures so far.

FOUR! Runs are flowing freely here at the Adelaide Oval. Short from Yasir Shah. Warner is not going to miss that. He might even put it away in his sleep. He gets on his back foot and pulls it through square leg for a boundary. Moves to 194 with that.
Tossed up delivery on off, Warner drives it through covers. The batsmen get two runs. 350 up for Australia.
Floated delivery on off, Warner plays it to cover.
FOUR! Brilliant batting this from Warner. Yasir gives this one air on off, Warner comes down the track and lofts it over wide long on with the spin for a boundary.

150 FOR MARNUS LABUSCHAGNE! He has continued from where he left off at 'Gabba! This has been a fine knock from the right hander. He will now look to convert this into his maiden double hundred. Missed that in the first Test and he would be eager to get it in this Test. He shows his bat to the crowd who rise up to applaud his knock. He then hugs Warner. The sight we have seen a lot of times in this Test. Floated on middle, Marnus flicks it behind square on the leg side to achieve this milestone.
Short delivery on off, Warner cuts it through point. The batsmen cross ends.
Tossed up delivery on off, David plays it towards covers for a single.
Flighted delivery on middle, Labuschagne sweeps it towards square leg. The batsmen take a run.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
Floated delivery on middle, Marnus flicks it to mid-wicket.
Flighted delivery on off, Warner drives it through mid off. The batsmen take a single.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Warner flicks it to mid-wicket.
Floated on off, Warner strokes it to cover and keeps the strike.
Loopy and shorter on off, Warner defends it off the back foot.

Direct hit and it would have been close. Floated on off, Labuschagne flicks it towards mid on and calls for a quick single. The fielder there has a shy at the bowler's end as Marnus scampers through. The fielder does not score a direct hit at the bowler's end.
Follows the boundary up with a calm finish.

FOUR! Excellent use of the feet from Labuschagne. Floated on off, Marnus comes down the track and takes the risk of going aerial. He does not time it to perfection but times it well to go over cow corner region for a boundary.
Flighted leg spinner on off, Labuschagne defends it back to the bowler.
Loopy delivery on off, Labuschagne drives it through covers. The batsmen take a run.
Flighted delivery on middle, Marnus blocks it off the back foot.
Tossed up delivery on leg, Labuschagne sweeps it towards fine leg. The batsmen pick up a couple.
Floated delivery on middle, Warner flicks it towards square leg for a single.
FOUR! That is put away! Loose delivery from Ifthikhar. It is a drag down, Warner is quick to pounce on it and pull it through mid-wicket for a boundary. Australia continuing from where they left off.
Flighted delivery on off, Warner defends it off the front foot.
Just a solitary over for Musa to start the day. Iftikhar Ahmed is into the attack. 8-0-30-0, his figures in this Test so far.
FOUR! Lovely shot. Leg spinner on off, it is slightly short. Labuschagne uses his wrist and whips it against the spin through mid-wicket for a boundary. Moves to 140 with that.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
Flighted delivery on off, Marnus defends it off the front foot.
Floated delivery on middle, David nudges it towards square leg for a run.
Tossed up delivery on off, Labuschagne drives it through covers. The batsmen cross ends.
Flighted delivery on middle, Warner flicks it towards square leg. The batsmen take a single.
Fuller on off, Warner pushes it to cover and takes a quick single to keep the strike. 11 off Musa's first over of the day.

Another good shot. Length ball on off, Labuschagne keeps his eyes on the ball and punches it through covers from right beneath his eyes through covers. The fielder chasing from cover cleans it up before the ropes saving a run for his side.
Fuller on the stumps, Labuschagne calmly blocks it.
Good shot. Length ball around off, Marnus gets on his back foot and punches it through covers for a couple.

FOUR! Labuschagne is underway for the day! Good length ball around off, Labuschagne looks to defend but the ball moves away. It takes the outside edge of the bat and squeezes away past gully for a boundary.

Mammoth stand! Good length ball around off, Warner strokes it towards point and looks for two. Marnus takes a single and calls a loud no for the second. Good call and with that the 300-run stand comes up.
Muhammad Musa to partner Yasir Shah from the other end.
Yasir bowls a yorker to end the over. It is on off, Labuschagne digs it out. 5 off the first over of the day.
Tossed up on middle and off, Labuschagne starts his innings with a solid defense first up.
Darted on the pads, Warner flicks it to square leg and gets a single.

FOUR! First runs off the day and Warner gets thing going with a boundary. Yasir gives this air but bowls it short outside off. Warner gets on his back foot and punches it against the spin through covers for a boundary.
Floated on off, Warner pushes it to mid on.
Yasir starts with a slightly quicker ball down the leg side. Warner looks to sweep but misses.

We are all set to begin Day 2! The Pakistan players are out on the field. Overnight batsmen, David Warner and Marnus Labuschagne walk out to resume their innings. Yasir Shah to start the day with the ball for Pakistan.

Welcome to the coverage of Day 2 of this second Test between Australia and Pakistan. The hosts are sitting in the driver's seat having scored 302 in just 73 overs in a reduced day's play on Day 1. David Warner and Marnus Labuschagne are unbeaten on 166 and 126 respectively and the duo will be eyeing their double hundreds putting Australia further in command. It was a timid bowling effort from the hosts and they will need to be much better with the strawberry. Just a solitary wicket on Day 1 shows how far they are already in this Test. Pakistan will need to find some inspiration and try and find a way to fight back in this game. Will they be able to do it?
... Day 2, First session ...

So that is it from the Day 1. What is in store for us on Day 2? Will the pair of Warner and Labuschagne build on their tons and pile on the misery or will Pakistan find some source of inspiration and find a way back in this game? Join us on Saturday, 30th November for Day 2 of this Test. There will be a 30 minute early start. The game will begin at 1330 Local (0300 GMT). Hope to see you then. Till then, cheers!

It was a challenging and a tiring day for the visitors. Shaheen Afridi was the only bowler who got a wicket. He was the only one who actually looked threatening. Mohammad Abbas bowled consistent lines and lengths but his lack of pace meant the pair saw him off easily. The spinners did not have a good time either as there was hardly any purchase off the surface for them. Muhammad Musa had a very tough outing on his debut going for about 5.5 rpo. All-in-all it was a forgetful outing for the tourists.

Excellent day's play for the hosts! Everything apart from Joe Burns' early wicket went their way. After opting to bat the hosts got off to a tough start having lost Joe Burns. Warner and Labuschagne then took their time out in the middle. The duo fought out the tough phase and then started to score at a brisk rate. After a delayed start to the second session, the pair continued their work and just like the first Test both Warner and Labuschagne scored brilliant tons.
Warner says that Labuschagne's knock in Queensland was outstanding and was exceptional in this innings as well. Further goes on to say that they will look to do the same on Day 2 as well.
Labuschagne says it was surreal and it was great to bat with Warner at the other end. Smiles and says that they run hard and hopes they can build on this on Day 2.
Marnus Labuschagne and David Warner walk out with smiles on their face. The duo is caught down for a quick chat.
Ends the day with a full delivery on off, Labuschagne blocks it to cover. STUMPS ON DAY 1.
Fullish delivery on off, Labuschagne is solid in defense. 1 more ball left in the day.
Good length ball on off, Warner pushes this to cover and takes a single.
Comes around the wicket and bowls a full delivery outside off, David lets the ball go to the keeper.
FOUR! Poor bowling from Musa! Full delivery outside off, Warner stands in crease and drives it through point for another boundary.
Starts with a bouncer outside off, Warner sways away from it.
Muhammad Musa is back on. 12-1-66-0 are his figures so far.
Loopy ball on middle, Marnus defends it back to the bowler.
Short ball outside off, David punches this towards cover and gives Labuschagne the strike.
Flatter delivery on middle, Labuschagne works it to deep mid-wicket and picks up another single.
Floated ball on middle and leg, Marnus pushes it to mid-wicket.
Flighted delivery on leg, Marnus looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head.
Tossed up delivery on off, Warner drives it towards mid off. The batsmen take a single.
Full delivery on the pads, Warner tucks it to fine leg and takes a single.
Flatter delivery on middle, Labuschagne pushes it to long on and picks up a single.
The batsman works it down the leg side. They pick up a single.
Tossed up ball on middle, Marnus works it to mid-wicket where Imam-ul-Haq makes a diving stop. The ball rolls towards mid on and the batters take a single.
Flighted ball on middle, Warner flicks it towards the leg side and takes a single.

Full delivery on middle, Warner bends on his knees and sweeps it with power through square leg. Iftikhar Ahmed hares across from fine leg and makes a good sliding stop. The batters manage to take a couple.
Flatter delivery on middle, Marnus works it to square leg for nothing.
Tossed up ball on middle, Warner tucks it to square leg and takes a single.
Floated ball outside off, Warner looks to defend this one but it goes off the outside edge towards third man for a couple.
Flatter delivery outside off, Warner shoulders arms to this one.
On off, pushed towards mid off.
Flighted ball on off, Warner pushes it to cover.
A single to end one more good over for Australia! On the pads, it is worked through square leg for one.

FOUR! Brings up his 150 in style! The crowd is up on its feet again to applaud the effort. He has also upped the ante now. Back-to-back boundaries for him. This is full and around off, Warner creams it wide of long off and it gets to the boundary.
FOUR! Swept and swept brilliantly! A little too straight by Shah. Warner gets down on one knee and sweeps it through backward square leg for a boundary.
Leading edge but a run! Slower through the air and on the pads, ML looks to flick it against the turn but it goes off the leading edge through point for one.
On middle, this is kept out nicely.

Better throw and Marnus Labuschagne would have been a goner. Floated on the stumps, Labuschagne flicks it through square leg and looks for two. Warner responds but Imam-ul-Haq gets to the ball quickly. He sends a throw at the keeper's end where Labuschagne puts in a dive but he is short of his crease. The throw though is a poor one which Rizwan fails to collect.
Tossed up on middle, Marnus defends it to get through the over.
Tossed up on middle and leg, Labuschagne sweeps it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Off spinner on the pads, Marnus flicks it with the turn to square leg.
On the pads, Labuschagne strokes it to mid on.
Flighted on off and middle, Warner pushes it towards cover-point for one.
Floated on off, there is some extra bounce on this one. Warner looks to defend but it goes to the off side off the outer half of his bat.
Short ball outside off, Marnus rocks on his back foot and punches the ball to the off side.
Floated ball outside off, Labuschagne looks to defend off the back foot but gets beaten due to the spin on it.

NOT OUT! A poor review from Pakistan! There is an inside edge on this one. Yasir Shah bowls a flighted ball on off, Warner goes to sweep but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The ball rolls towards the leg side. Yasir appeals but the umpire shakes his head. After some thought and discussion, Azhar goes for the review. The Ultra Edge rolls in and it shows that there is a little inside edge on that one. The ball rolls towards the leg side and the batters take a single.

Pakistan have opted to take the review for an LBW! This is the first time they have half a chance and they have taken the review. Warner looks to sweep but the ball goes off his pad. Hot Spot rolls in and it shows that there is a little inside edge onto the pads. Pakistan lose one of their two reviews.
Full delivery on middle, Warner works it towards the leg side.
Flatter delivery down the leg side, Warner looks to flick it but misses it. Rizwan fails to collect it cleanly as well.
Full delivery on off, Labuschagne drives it to extra cover and takes a single.
Yasir Shah is back into the attack. 11-0-66-0 are his figures so far.
Full delivery on middle, Warner blocks it out.
Another flat delivery outside off, ML guides it to third man and takes a single.
Flatter delivery on off, Warner defends it to cover and takes a single.
Tossed up ball outside off, Labuschagne drives it to long off for a single.
Short ball on middle and leg, Warner flicks it to square leg and takes a single.
Flatter delivery on off, Marnus pushes it to long on and takes a single.
Full delivery outside off, Warner pushes it to cover.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Labuschagne flicks it to fine leg and crosses over for a single.
Full delivery on middle, Marnus defends it to the leg side.
Low full toss on off, Warner drives it to cover and takes a single.
Full delivery on middle, Warner drives it to mid on.
Good length ball outside off, Labuschagne guides it towards gully where the fielder gets a hand on it. The ball rolls to backward point and the batters take a single.
No Ball! Good length ball on middle, Marnus defends it onto the pitch. Shaheen has overstepped and the umpire signals a no ball.
Loopy ball on middle, Labuschagne pushes it to mid on and takes a single.
Short ball outside off, Warner punches this to deep cover and brings up the 250-run stand between the two with a single.
Tossed up ball on middle, David blocks it back to the bowler.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.
Fullish ball on off, Warner pushes it to mid off for nothing.
Bowls a flighted ball on off, Warner defends it to cover.
Iftikhar Ahmed is back.
Very full on off, Labuschagne pushes it to mid off.
Bouncer! It is away from the body, Marnus does not play at it but once again practices the pull once the ball is behind.
Back of a length ball on off, Marnus defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Nicely played. Back of a length ball around off, Marnus just guides it to the third man fence for a boundary.
Length ball around off, Warner hops on to defend it but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The ball goes to the off side and they take a single.
Good length ball pitching on leg, Warner looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is a stifled appeal but nothing says the umpire.
On off, pushed towards point by Marnus.
FOUR! This is what happens when a part-timer comes on. Azhar bowls a rank long hop on middle, Labuschagne rocks on his back foot and pulls it through mid-wicket for the second boundary of the over.
Floated ball on middle, Warner flicks it towards the leg side for a single.
Full delivery on middle, Warner plays it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Poor delivery! Short ball outside off, Warner rocks on his back foot and slams it through covers for a boundary.
Starts with a short delivery on off, Warner punches it to the keeper.
Azhar Ali, the skipper, brings himself into the attack.
Slower ball bowled at around 116 kph. Warner tucks it to the leg side and keeps the strike.
Full on off and middle, Warner strokes it to the left of the bowler. Shaheen gets a hand to it but cannot stop it cleanly. Does not cost any extra run.
Good length ball on off, Warner glances it to the on side and gets a couple.
Full outside off, David pushes it to cover and shouts a loud no.
FOUR! Australia piling up the pain here. Good length ball outside off, Warner slams it through third man for a boundary.
Starts his new spell with a bouncer. It is around off, Warner sways away from it.
Shaheen Afridi is back for another burst. 15-4-32-1, his figures so far.
Short delivery outside off, Labuschagne punches this off the back foot to the off side.
Fullish ball on off, Labuschagne drives it to covers.
FOUR! Beautifully played! Floated ball on middle, Labuschagne lunges forward and whips it through mid-wicket for another boundary. Pakistan currently have no clue as where to bowl at the moment.
Floated on off, Marnus keeps it out.

HUNDRED FOR LABUSCHAGNE! His second in Tests and both of them have come in this series. What a beautiful knock this has been. Tossed up on middle, Marnus flicks it through mid-wicket and gets a couple. He raises his bat and removes his helmet as he gets a huge applause from the crowd and his teammates. With a huge smile on his face he gets a big hug from his partner. Missed out on his double hundred in the last game, he will now look to fulfill that in this Test.

FOUR! Labuschagne will have to wait for some more for his hundred. Yasir bowls a flighted ball on off, Labuschagne comes down the track and lifts this over mid off for a boundary. It looked like a six at first but the umpires go to check and the ball had just bounced in front of the rope.
Short ball, ML pulls it to deep square leg and keeps the strike.
Extra bounce off the surface for Musa. It is around off, Warner looks to defend but gets surprised by the bounce on this one. It goes off the outer half of his bat through cover-point for one.
Hits the deck hard around the body, Marnus pulls it to the on side for one.
Another short ball. This one is a good bouncer as it is around the eyes of Labuschagne. Marnus keeps it down by hopping up.
Back of a length ball but this one does not raise. It is around the waist region. Warner takes his eyes off and pulls it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Short ball around off, Labuschagne pulls it with power but there is a man in the deep so just a single.
Shorter in length outside off, Labuschagne punches it off the back foot to cover and takes a single.
Flatter delivery outside off, Marnus guides it towards third man and takes a couple.
Flighted ball on middle, Labuschagne defends it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Tossed up ball outside off, Labuschagne rocks on his back foot and guides it through gully for another boundary.
Flatter delivery outside off, Warner cuts it towards the off side and takes a single.

MISFIELD AND FOUR! Shaheen Afridi is not having a good day in terms of fielding! Shah bowls a flighted ball outside off, Warner drives it through cover and Afridi is chasing after it. Shaheen first goes to pick it up but kicks the ball into the cover fence.
Yasir Shah to bowl after the break. No wicket for his 44 runs so far.

Drinks Break! Australia continue to dominate this game. Warner and Labuschagne have added 201 without actually breaking any sweat. Pakistan need to find some inspiration from somewhere. They are looking very pedestrian at the moment.
Short ball on middle, Marnus punches it off the back foot.

OVERTHROWS! Full delivery outside off, Warner drives it to cover. Marnus Labuschagne takes a few steps ahead and Yasir Shah at cover has a shy at the bowler's end. He hits but Marnus is well in. The ball rolls towards mid-wicket allowing the batsman to take a single.
Musa keeps on bowling bouncers and Warner seems happy to keep ducking under it.
Another bouncer but this is bowled down the leg side, Warner ducks under it.
Short ball on middle, Marnus pulls it towards deep mid-wicket and picks up a single.
WIDE! BOUNCER! Musa bowls this way over the head of Labuschagne. Marnus lets it go to the keeper. The umpire signals it a wide.
Short delivery outside off, Labuschagne guides it to gully for nothing.
Away from the off pole, Warner leaves it alone to get through the over.
Good length ball outside off. Warner shoulders arms to it. The ball falls forward of Rizwan who dives and looks to stop it. He fails to do so cleanly but that does not cost any run.
Full on off, Davey defends it towards mid on.
Length ball outside off, Warner cuts it between point and cover and gets a couple as the man from point cleans it up.
On the fourth stump line, Warner offers a confident leave.
Good length ball on off, Warner defends it with a straight bat.
Mohammad Abbas is back into the attack. Wicketless so far.
Full delivery on middle, Marnus flicks it towards mid-wicket for nothing. An expensive over comes to an end from Muhammad Musa.
Good length ball outside off, Warner punches it to deep point and takes a single.

On a length on off, Marnus defends it to cover and calls Warner for a quick single. The fielder at cover fails to collect it cleanly. Had he picked it up and had a shy at the keeper's end, it could have been close.

FOUR! Another one which has been thrashed! Musa is not learning here! Short delivery on middle, Labuschagne pulls it with ease in front of square to pick up the second boundary of the over. The fielder comes across in an attempt to stop the ball from reaching the fence but he is unable to reach it on time.

FOUR! Hammered! Muhammad Musa is not having a good debut so far. Bowls it short on middle which does not rise enough. Labuschagne rocks on his back foot and pulls it with disdain into the deep mid-wicket fence.
Full delivery outside off, Warner drives it with power to deep cover and takes a single.
Muhammad Musa is back on. 9-1-47-0, his numbers so far on his debut Test.
Tossed up on off, Marnus flicks it with good wrist work but straight to mid-wicket.
Flighted on off, Warner sweeps it to square leg for one.
Tossed up on off, Labuschagne milks it through covers for one.
Follows the boundary with a single. Sweeps this one towards backward square leg for one.
FOUR! Short and wide, Warner is ready to punish it. It is around off, Warner hangs back on his back foot and cuts it with power through point for a boundary.
Floated leg spinner on off, Warner flicks it on the bounce which hits the man at square leg.
EDGED AND FOUR! Lucky but runs nonetheless. Good length ball outside off, Marnus looks to defend it but it goes off the outside edge past the gully region and into the fence.
Full delivery outside off, Warner drives it through covers and takes three before the fielder can clean it up.

LEG BYE! Full delivery on the pads, Marnus looks to flick it but gets hit on the pads. Abbas appeals but the umpire shakes his head. The ball rolls towards the leg side and the batters steal a leg bye.
Good length ball on middle, Labuschagne works it to mid-wicket.
Full delivery outside off, Warner pushes it to cover.
Good length ball on off, Warner looks to defend but it goes off the pads towards the off side.
Loopy ball on middle, Warner flicks it towards deep square leg and retains the strike.
Tossed up ball on middle, Warner lunges forward and defends it back to the bowler.
Flatter delivery on off, Warner defends it onto the pitch.
Tossed up ball on middle, Labuschagne flicks it to mid-wicket and takes a single.

There it is! Back-to-back centuries for David Warner. What a sublime knock this has been from the southpaw. Century no. 23 for David in Tests. He leaps and punches the air in celebration in trademark Warner style. Shorter on middle and leg, Warner dabs it towards backward point and rushes to the other end for a quick single. He collides with Yasir at the bowler's end and his bat is off his hand but that does not matter as he runs towards the crowd and punches the air in joy. The Bull will now look to convert this into a bigger one. Maybe even a double hundred.
Flighted ball on off, Marnus pushes it to mid off and givces Warner the strike.
And there gets Warner...through the over. On a length outside off, Warner leaves it with a Steven Smith-esque leave.
The wait goes no. Good length ball on middle and leg, Warner tucks it to the on side.
Abbas wants Warner to drive but David says no and leaves it alone.
The crowd is getting anxious. Back of a length ball on off, Warner dabs it down towards backward point and once again does not get the single.
Length ball on off, Warner pushes it to cover and hangs around on 99.
Keeps the crowd waiting. Good length ball on off, Warner defends it towards cover. Marnus looks for a quick single but David is in no hurry as he shouts a loud no to his partner.
Short delivery on the pads, Warner sweeps it to backward square leg and retains the strike for the next over with his score on 99.
On middle, blocked by David.
Flatter delivery on middle, Warner works it towards mid-wicket.
Floated ball on middle, Warner defends it back to the bowler.
Tossed up ball down the leg side, Warner bends to sweep it but fails to get any bat on it.
Full delivery outside off, Warner drives it through covers and picks up a couple. Moves to 98 with that.
Fullish and around off again, Marnus pushes it towards cover.
Fullish and on off, driven towards mid off.
Good length ball around off, Labuschagne defends off the front foot.
On middle, Marnus tucks it towards square leg.
Around off, Labuschagne taps it towards point and thinks for a single initially but decides against it in the end.
Shortish length ball outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms.
Mohammad Abbas is back on. He replaces Shaheen Afridi. 15-4-46-0 are his figures so far.
Short delivery outside off, Warner camps on his back foot and punches it past the diving fielder at cover for a couple.
Flat delivery on middle, Warner works it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up ball on middle, Warner defends it back to the bowler.
Flatter delivery on middle and leg, Warner flicks it to fine leg for a couple. The fielder throws it to the keeper but Warner makes a good dive to get in.
Short delivery outside off, Marnus punches it through covers off the back foot for another single.
Floated ball on middle, Warner pushes it down to long on and picks up a single.
Around off on a length, Labuschagne blocks it out.
Fullish this time around off, Marnus strokes it back to the bowler.
In the channel outside off, Labuschagne covers his stumps and lets it be.
Just behind good length and closer to off pole. Labuschagne blocks it off the back foot towards mid off.
Good length ball outside off, Warner taps it towards point and takes a quick single.
Shortish length ball angled into the left-hander. Warner defends it out.
Tossed up ball on middle, Labuschagne defends it back to the bowler.
Flatter delivery outside off, Marnus leaves the ball alone.
BEATEN! Lovely stuff! Flighted ball outside off, Labuschagne looks to defend it but gets beaten.
Short ball outside off, Labuschagne pushes it to point.
Shorter delivery outside off, Marnus plays the square cut but finds the fielder at point.

Time for some innovation! Yasir bowls a flighted ball on middle, Warner plays the reverse sweep through third man and picks up three. Shaheen runs after it from point and makes a good sliding stop. Moves into the 90s now does Warner.
Yasir Shah replaces Iftikhar Ahmed. 4-0-21-0 are his figures so far.
Length ball outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball outside off, Marnus leaves it alone.
Good ball. Shaheen hits the deck hard around off, Labuschagne looks to defend but misses.

Shaheen is lucky there. He delivers a full toss on middle and leg. Warner flicks it through mid-wicket and looks for two. Labuschagne says no for the second as the fielder in the deep was quick to get there.
Full on middle and off, David flicks it straight to square leg.
Good length ball on off, Warner defends it off the back foot.
Short ball on off, Marnus blocks it out.
On middle, defended by Labuschagne.
Floated ball on middle, Marnus flicks it towards the leg side and takes a couple. 150-run stand is up between the two.
Shorter delivery outside off, Warner punches this off the back foot towards the off side and takes a single.

Shorter delivery outside off, Labuschagne makes a little bit of room and cuts it through covers. Shaheen hares after it and this time manages to clean it up before it reaches the ropes. The batters take three.
Shorter delivery outside off, Warner punches this to deep cover and takes a single.
Good length delivery outside off, Marnus shoulders arms to this one.
Very full delivery on off, Warner digs it out to point and calls Labuschagne for a quick single.
Back of a length delivery on middle, David defends it back to Shaheen.
On a length on middle, David blocks it onto the pitch.
On middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Full delivery outside off, Warner drives this through cover and picks up a couple before the fielder can clean it up.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Flighted ball on middle, Warner flicks it towards the leg side and takes a single.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.

FOUR! What happened there? It looks like Shaheen was unable to see the ball for a bit. Short of a length delivery outside off, Warner rocks on his back foot and punches it towards deep cover where Afridi is unable to see the ball clearly and allows the ball go through and into the fence. The same happened with the red ball in the 'Gabba and it has happened here as well.
Another flat delivery on off, Labuschagne flicks it towards short fine leg. The batters take a single.
Starts with a flat delivery on off, Labuschagne stands back and pushes it to short mid-wicket.
Iftikhar Ahmed will bowl from the other end.
Full delivery on middle, Warner flicks it to mid-wicket.
Another one on a length, David is solid in defense.
Good length delivery on off, Warner defends it towards mid off.
Full delivery on middle, David blocks it out.
On a length on middle, Warner defends it back to the bowler off the back foot.

FOUR! Lucky start for David Warner after the break. Shaheen starts with a full delivery outside off, Warner goes for a drive but it goes off the outside edge and uppishly towards third man for a boundary. Afridi has been bowling well but hasn't found any luck so far.

We are back for the final session of the day! Pakistan players make their way out to the middle and take their respective fielding positions. David Warner and Marnus Labuschagne also make their way out to resume their innings. Shaheen Afridi will start the proceedings for the visitors.
... Day 1, Session 3 ...

Warner says that they thought it would swing a little bit under lights and hence they were very disciplined. On his fifty, Warner says he is happy to have got it and says they have stuck to their plans.

A solid session for the Aussies. The second session took its sweet time to begin as rain played spoilsport. Warner and Labuschagne were unaffected by the extended break as the duo continued from where they left off. The duo got to their respective 50s and stretched their partnership to 131. 5 bowlers were used by the visitors with the spin duo of Iftikhar and Yasir Shah bowling just 5 overs. Shaheen was once again impressive but could not get the breakthrough. Will Australia end the day showing their dominance or will Pakistan finish the day on the front foot? Join us after the break to find out but before that David Warner is caught down for a quick chat.
Flatter delivery on off, Warner defends it to cover and takes off for a quick single. With that it is DINNER ON DAY 1.
FOUR! Beautifully played! Yasir bowls a flighted ball outside off, Warner lunges forward and creams the drive through mid off for his 10th boundary of the innings.
Tossed up ball on middle, Warner works it to mid on.
Loopy ball on off, David blocks it out to the off side.
Flatter delivery down the leg side, Warner pads this one out.
Floated ball on middle, Warner works it to mid-wicket.
On the pads, Labuschagne flicks it to square leg. 2 off Iftikhar's first.
Tossed up on off, Labuschagne comes down the track and pushes it back to the left of Iftikhar.
Slightly shorter on off, Labuschagne blocks it off his back foot.
Tossed up on off, ML defends it off the front foot.
Floated around middle, Labuschagne flicks it with the spin behind square on the leg side for a couple.
Iftikhar starts with a flighted delivery on off, Marnus watchfully defends it.
Iftikhar Ahmed is brought on now.
Shorter in length down the leg side, Warner looks to flick it but misses it.
Loopy ball on off, Marnus prods forward and drives it wide of mid off for a single.
Flatter delivery on off, Labuschagne defends it to point.
Tossed up ball on middle, Warner pushes it to long on and takes a single.
Flatter delivery down the leg side, Warner does not fiddle with it.
Floated ball on off, Warner pushes it to cover.

FOUR! Beautiful, absolutely beautiful! Musa has no clue what to bowl at the moment. Short ball on middle, Labuschagne camps on his back foot and hammers the pull through mid-wicket for another boundary.
Musa goes full this time and bowls it on middle, Marnus prods forward and defends it back to the bowler.
On a length on middle, Labuschagne rocks on his back foot and blocks it out.
Good length ball on off, Marnus defends it back to the bowler.

FOUR! FIFTY! 6th in Test cricket for Marnus Labuschagne. He continues to put big strides in Test cricket since he came on as a concussion substitute for Steven Smith in the Ashes. This has been another excellent knock from the youngster. Coming to the ball, short ball outside off, Marnus rocks on his back foot and guides it through gully for a boundary. Another hundred on offer here?
On a good length and outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms to this one.
Flighted on the pads, Warner flicks it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Warner takes the aerial route! Flighted on off, Warner gets down on one knee and slog sweeps it over mid-wicket. The ball bounces inside the ropes and goes away to the fence.
Shorter on off, Warner cuts it to point.
Excellent running! Floated on the pads, Labuschagne flicks it fine down the leg side. Warner and Marnus are both quick between the wickets. They run hard and take three.
FOUR! Good footwork. Yasir gives this one air on middle, Labuschagne maintains his balance and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Floated on middle and off, Marnus flicks it to mid on.
Full delivery outside off, Warner lunges forward and drives it to cover for a couple.
On a length outside off, Warner looks to push it to the off side but it hits the inside edge of the bat onto the pads and then onto the pitch.
Good length ball on middle, David plays it back to the bowler.
BOUNCER! A good one at that! Musa bowls it with good pace on middle, Warner ducks under it.
Full delivery on off, David pushes it to mid off and looks for a single but decides against it.
Full delivery on off, Warner defends it to the off side.
Flighted ball on middle, Marnus works it to mid-wicket.
Played to the point region by the batsman. They pick up a single.
Full delivery on middle, Warner plays it back to the bowler.

Shorter in length on middle, Warner pulls it towards deep square leg. Shaheen runs across and fails to collect the ball cleanly. He recovers and stops the ball from reaching the fence. The batters take two and with this the 100-run stand is up between the two. After losing the wicket of Burns early on in the innings, these two have put in an excellent stand and are going comfortably at the moment.
Flat one on the leg stump, Warner stands back and whips it towards fine leg.
Yasir starts with a flighted leg spinner on the pads. Warner looks to flick but it goes off his thigh pad. Bit of purchase off the surface for him first up.
Finally leg spinner, Yasir Shah is introduced into the attack. Can the leggie spin his web and provide his skipper with a break through?
Good length delivery outside off, Marnus shoulders arms to this one.
Outside off, left alone by Marnus.
Short delivery on middle, Labuschagne pulls it with disdain towards deep mid-wicket. Imam-ul-Haq dives and makes a good stop but does not stop the batters from taking a couple.
Full delivery on middle, Warner pushes it to mid off and takes a single.

Full delivery outside off, Marnus drives it but the bat turns in his hand and that took the pace off the ball. It goes through cover and two fielders hare after it from cover and point respectively and stop the ball from reaching the ropes. The batters take three.
Fullish delivery outside off, Labuschagne lets it go back to the keeper.
Good length ball outside off, Warner shoulders arms to this one.

With Warner and Labuschagne being unaffected by Abbas' consistent lines and lengths and settled with the pacers it should be about time when Azhar Ali goes to Yasir Shah. Having said that we have hardly seen spinners operate in the twilight period of a Day/Night Test.
Full delivery on middle, Warner defends it back to the bowler.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Labuschagne tucks it to deep square leg and gives Warner the strike.
Shorter in length outside off, Marnus guides this to gully where Babar makes a good diving stop. Saves a few runs for his side.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Warner whips it to square leg and takes a single.
Fullish ball outside off, David shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on middle, Labuschagne pushes it to mid on. First maiden over for Muhammad Musa in international cricket.
Back of a length ball outside off, Marnus rocks on his back foot and punches this to cover.
Back of a length ball outside off, Labuschagne punches this towards point for nothing.
On a length outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery outside off, Labuschagne lets the ball go to the keeper.
Full delivery on off, Marnus looks to defend it but it goes off the outside edge towards gully. The fielder collects it on the bounce. No run.
Muhammad Musa is back into the attack. 5-0-31-0 are his figures so far.
Full delivery outside off, Warner makes another leave to the keeper.
Good length delivery on off, Warner pushes it to cover for nothing.
Fullish ball outside off, David leaves it alone.
Full delivery on the pads, Marnus works it through deep mid-wicket and gives Warner the strike.
Short of a length outside off angling in, Labuschagne does not fiddle with it and lets it go to Rizwan.
Full delivery on off, Marnus pushes it to mid off.
Good length ball outside off, David shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery way outside off, Warner shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on middle, David works it to mid on for nothing.
On a length on middle, Warner defends it back to Shaheen.
Very full delivery on middle, Warner pushes it to mid on. He wants the single but decides against it.
Back of a length ball on middle, Warner defends it onto the pitch.
Full delivery on off, Labuschagne defends it towards the off side.
Good length ball outside off, Labuschagne leaves the ball alone.
Fullish delivery outside off, Marnus does not fiddle with this one and lets the ball go to the keeper.
On a length on off, Marnus blocks it out.
Good length ball outside off, Marnus, in an unorthodox manner, leaves this alone.
Fullish ball on middle, Labuschagne works it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on off, Marnus looks to defend but it goes off the inside edge onto the pads. The ball rolls towards square leg and takes a single.
FOUR! Another poor delivery and Marnus Labuschagne makes full toll of it. Shaheen bowls a full delivery on middle and leg, Labuschagne whips it through mid-wicket for another boundary.
Full delivery on middle, Warner tucks it to square leg and picks up another single.
Short delivery on middle, Marnus pulls it towards deep mid-wicket and crosses over for a single.
On a length on middle, Marnus defends it out.
Good length delivery which is closer to the off stump, Labuschagne covers his stumps and makes a good leave.
Labuschagne flicks this good length ball on middle to deep square leg for a single.
Abbas bowls a good length ball on middle, Marnus defends it back to the bowler.

FOUR! Poor delivery but still had to be put away. Full delivery on the pads, Labuschagne will not miss out on these easy balls and he just flicks this in front of square for his fifth boundary of the innings.
On a length on middle, Marnus pushes it back to the bowler.
Good length ball on the pads, Warner flicks it to backward square leg and picks up a single.
Fullish delivery outside off, Warner leaves this one alone.
Full delivery on middle, Marnus punches this straight down the ground for a couple. Muhammad Musa from mid off races after it and cleans it up before it reaches the ropes.
Good length ball on the pads, Labuschagne works it to mid-wicket and shouts a loud 'wait on' to his partner.
Shaheen goes short this time on off, Marnus rocks on his back foot and pushes it to cover.
Good length ball outside off, Marnus shoulders arms to this one.
On a length on off, Marnus, this time, gets bat on it and defends it to cover.

BEATEN! Beautiful bowling this from Shaheen Afridi! Good length ball on off moving away from the batsman, Labuschagne looks to defend this one but the ball beats the outside edge of this one and into the mitts of the keeper.

SIX OVERTHROWS! Warner gets to his fifty with some luck! He continues his form in this series. 154 in the first Test and now he has got a fifty. He would be looking to convert this into another big one. Back of a length ball on off, Warner hops and looks to glance it to the on side. It goes behind square on the leg side after getting a thick inside edge. They look for two. The fielder has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. There is no one backing up and the fielder chasing it cannot stop it before the ball reaches the fence. He raises his bat and gets a hug from his partner. The crowd applaud his effort. 31st Test fifty for David Warner. He would look to convert this into another big daddy ton.
Another one on a length outside off, Warner shoulders arms to this one.
Good length ball outside off, Warner does not bother to play at that one and lets it go to the keeper.
Warner leaves this good length ball outside off alone.
On a length on middle, Warner pushes it back to the bowler.
Back of a length ball on middle, Warner hops and works it to square leg for a couple. The fielder from square leg hares after it and cleans it up.
Mohammad Abbas will bowl from the other end.

FOUR! Good length ball on off, Labuschagne looks to defend but the ball shapes away taking the outside edge of Marnus' willow. It squeezes between gully and second slip for a boundary. Streaky way to get the first runs of the session.
Now Marnus pushes it to cover.
Edged but safe. Fuller on off, Labuschagne looks to drive but gets a thick outside edge. It goes to the left of gully. Babar Azam there dives on that side and saves runs for his side.
Outside off, Marnus leaves it this time.
Good ball. Fuller around off it looks to be coming in but goes away after hitting the deck. Labuschagne looks to defend but gets beaten.
Shaheen starts with a pacy delivery outside off on a length. Labuschagne leaves it in an unorthodox manner to start by.

After a lengthy delay which looked like ages. We are finally about to start the second session of Day 1. The Pakistan players are in a huddle before they take their position in the field. David Warner and Marnus Labuschagne walk out to resume their innings. Shaheen Afridi to bowl the first over of the second session.

Update 1803 Local (0733 GMT) - Seems like it is time for the covers to go off. They are off and this time we are praying that it does not come back on. If there is no more rain then we are expected to start at 1815 Local (0745 GMT).

Update 1725 (0655 GMT) - The hide and seek with the rain continues. The covers come out again making it a painful sight for all the cricketing fans. We have started to lose overs for the day now but that can be covered up in the remaining days with early starts.

Update 1719 Local (0649 GMT) - Bringing you some good news but this time with my fingers crossed. The covers are coming off and the outfield is being roped. We are optimistic so let's hope that we can finally start the second session.

Update 1700 Local (0630 GMT) - Finally second session of Day 1 is about to start. Warner and Labuschagne walk out to resume their innings. Wish I could say that. In fact there is a bad news, the covers are back on as the heavens have opened up again.

Update 1643 Local (0613 GMT) - We have some good news! It has stopped raining and looks like the skies are clearing. Hopefully we should get started soon. Well, the second session will finally begin at 1700 Local (0630 GMT).
Nothing positive to update. The covers are still firmly in place.
We do not have a good news to begin this second session. The covers are still on which means we will have a delayed start. Let's hope that the rain stops and we resume as soon as possible.
... Day 1, Session 2 ...

Shaheen Afridi is caught down for a quick chat. Shaheen says that the weather is good and there is a little bit of movement off the deck. On his first wicket in pink ball Test, Shaheen tells he is very happy with his effort.

Pakistan got off to a good start with the ball. Shaheen Afridi was the pick of the bowlers in this session. He was the only bowler to get into the wickets column. Abbas was good with the line and length but failed to hit the stumps with his bowling. Debutant Musa Khan has had a tough start, giving away 31 runs in his 5 overs. The visitors need to improve their efforts and need to find a way to get rid of this partnership. Will they be able to do it? Before that let's see what Shaheen Afridi has to say about this session as he is down for a quick chat.

Early Tea has been called for here. Little drizzles has seen the umpires call for early Tea. A solid Test match session here in Adelaide. After opting to bat, the hosts got off to a poor start losing Joe Burns early. Warner and Labuschagne started off cautiously. The duo has found their feet and have started to get going especially the southpaw. They have added an unbeaten 62-run stand and will look to build on this.
On a good length on middle, David defends it out.
Good length delivery on middle, Warner defends it off the back foot.

FOUR! Classic David Warner. Good length ball outside off, Warner gets on his front foot. He leans forward and drives it with ease right through the middle of his bat for a boundary. This is Warner at his best!
Good length delivery outside off, David shoulders arms to this one.
Outside off, David leaves it alone.
Good length delivery on middle, Warner blocks it off the back foot.
On a good length on off, Marnus defends it off the front foot.
Length delivery outside off, David pushes it towards point. The batsmen take a run.
Good length delivery on off, Warner defends it to point.
Outside off, Warner offers no shot to this one.
On a good length on off, Warner blocks it off the back foot.
Length delivery on middle, Labuschagne flicks it towards mid-wicket. The batsmen cross ends.
Shaheen Afridi is back. 6-3-8-1, his numbers so far.
Outside off, David lets it go.
Good length delivery outside off, David shoulders arms to this one.
Again outside off, Warner offers no shot to this one.
Outside off, Warner leaves it alone.
On a good length on off, Warner defends it to covers.
On a length on off, Labuschagne drives it towards covers. The batsmen take a quick run.

What would Azhar Ali be thinking right now? Whether his communication skills are good enough or not. If he keeps a field for full balls, so that his bowlers can try and swing the strawberry, they bowl short. And if he keeps the field back, the short length is too short, not even coming up to chest height. And here is one important stat - Off all balls that Mohammad Abbas has bowled today, NOT ONE would have hit the stumps. He has been consistent with his line but a fraction too short. Having said that, he needs to make the batsmen play more.
Hits the deck hard around off. The ball nips back in. David looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the thigh pad.
No Ball. Musa oversteps again. He needs to be careful here. Good length ball outside off, Warner leaves it alone.
No Ball. Musa oversteps again. Full on off, Marnus flicks it to the on side for one.
Fuller outside off, Marnus leaves it alone.
FOUR! Labuschagne brings up the 50-run stand in style. Back of a length ball around off, Marnus pulls it with disdain through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Good length ball around off, Warner late cuts it to third man for one.
FOUR! Warner starting to find the fence more frequently now. Loose delivery from Musa. Length ball outside off, Warner waits for it and cuts it through backward point for a boundary.
Uppish but safe. Short ball around off, Labschagne pulls it uppishly. There is a man in the deep at mid-wicket but luckily for Marnus it falls short of him.
Good length delivery on middle, Warner blocks it off the back foot.
On a good length on off, Warner keeps it out.

FOUR! Excellent hand-eye coordination from Warner. Abbas bowls it short outside off, Warner gets on his back foot and punches it right under his eye line through covers. The outfield is slow but the ball still beats the chasing fielder to the fence.
Good length delivery outside off, Warner covers the line of the stumps and lets it go.
Outside off, Warner offers no shot to this one.
Length delivery on middle, Labuschagne flicks it through square leg. The batsmen take a single.
On a good length delivery on off, Warner taps it to point.
Short delivery on middle, Labuschagne pulls it through mid-wicket for a run.
Outside off again, Marnus leaves it alone.
Outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms to this one.
On a good length and outside off, Labuschagne taps it to point.
Short of a length delivery, Warner pulls it towards mid-wicket for a single.
On a good length on off, Marnus blocks it well.
Length delivery on middle, Labuschagne flicks it to mid-wicket.
On a good length on middle, Marnus defends it out.
On a good length on off, Labuschagne defends it off the front foot.
Outside off, Marnus shoulders arms to this one.
Good length delivery on off, Marnus looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.

Excellent ball. Yorker from Musa on off. Warner jams it out. He is unaware where the ball is. It is on the leg side on the pitch. Warner feels that it might go onto hit the stumps but he misses his kick of the ball and ends up getting himself nutmegged.
Bowls a bouncer again, David lets it sail through to the keeper.
Bowls a bumper, Warner does well to duck under it.
Follows the boundary with a calm leave to this length ball outside off.
FOUR! Slammed! Length ball outside off, there is width on offer. Warner transfers his weight onto his back foot and cuts it through backward point for a boundary.
Short delivery outside off, Warner cuts it towards point where the fielder  tries to stop it but it goes through him. The batsmen get two runs.
FOUR! Nice shot. Full delivery on middle, Labuschagne flicks it through square leg for a boundary.
Good length delivery on off, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Labuschagne offers no shot to this one.
Full delivery on middle, Marnus flicks it to mid-wicket.
Keeper is up now. Labuschagne has been standing well outside his crease for Abbas. So Rizwan has decided to stand up so that Marnus has to come back inside the crease.
Good length delivery outside off, Marnus leaves it alone.
Outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms to this one.
Mohammad Abbas is back on. 5-2-15-0, his figures so far.
Bowls a bumper, David does well to duck under it.
Bowls a bouncer outside off, Warner watches it sail through to the keeper.
Full delivery outside off, Warner drives it to point where Imam-ul-Haq makes a fine stop.
Good length delivery on off, Warner defends it off the back foot.

FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Warner. Musa after being hit for a boundary gives a typical fast bowler's respone. He bangs it in short. Warner is ready for it and he upper cuts it over the third man region for a boundary.

FOUR! Crunched away! Musa is guilty of overpitching around off, Warner with the form that he is in is not going to miss that. David gets on his front foot and slashes his drive through covers for a boundary.

Drinks! Good start to the session for the visitors. Shaheen Afridi has looked very good and has a wicket rightfully to his name. Abbas has been consistent not giving away anything. Australia have made a cautious start but would hope Warner and Labuschagne can see off the period and then build on it.
On a good length on middle, Marnus keeps it out.
Good length delivery on off, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
Good ball. Short ball around the body. Marnus takes his eyes off the ball and awkwardly looks to get away from it. It could have been dangerous but luckily it goes just over his shoulder.
Bowls a bouncer, Labuschagne ducks under it.
On a good length on off, Marnus defends it off the front foot.
Short delivery on middle, Warner pulls it through mid-wicket. The fielder chases the ball and does well to stop it. The batsmen get three runs.
Good length ball outside off, Marnus leaves it alone and then practices a late pull. He has been doing that a lot in this game.
Very full on middle, Labuschagne flicks it to the right of mid-wicket. The fielder there does well to save runs with a dive.
On the stumps, Marnus defends it with a straight bat.
Fuller on off, Labuschagne defends it off the front foot.

No Ball! This is a very good ball from Musa. Length ball bowled at around 143 kph. It is just outside off and zips away. Labuschagne is aware of his off stump and offers a good leave. Musa though has overstepped his line and it has been called a no ball.
Pulls back his length and bowls it around off. Warner hops and pushes it towards cover off his back foot and calls for a quick single.
Musa starts with a fuller delivery on off, Warner pushes it to cover. Not a lot of movement first up for the debutant.
First bowling change of the game. Debutant Muhammad Musa into the action now. He will bowl his first over in Test cricket. Let's see what we have in store.
Good length delivery outside off, Marnus does not bother to play at that.
Bowls a bouncer, Labuschagne watches it sail through to the keeper.
On a good length on middle, Marnus defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on middle, Labuschagne defends it off the front foot.
Outside off, Marnus lets it go.
On a good length and outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms to this one.
Outside off again, Warner leaves it alone.
Outside off, Warner lets it go.
Good length delivery on off, Warner blocks it off the back foot.
Outside off, David leaves it alone.
Length delivery on middle, Warner flicks it through square leg. The batsmen pick up a couple.

FOUR! Good shot this from Warner. Not a bad ball from Abbas. It is a back of a length delivery around off, Warner picks the length early. He lunges forward and drives it on the up through covers for a boundary. Warner slowly finding his stride here.
The umpires are having a word with Marnus Labuschagne. Looks like it is because he is running on the danger part of the pitch.
Outside off, Labuschagne does not bother to play at that.
Full delivery on middle, Marnus drives it back towards the bowler.
Good length delivery on off, Labuschagne defends it off the front foot.
Outside off again, Labuschagne shoulders arms  to this one.
Outside off, Marnus lets it go.
On a length on off, Warner taps it towards covers and takes a quick single. The fielder goes for a direct hit at the keeper's end but misses it.
On a good length on middle, Marnus looks to flick but gets a leading edge on this one. It goes towards covers safely.
Good length delivery on off, Marnus defends it off the back foot.

FOUR! Labuschagne is off the mark. Just like all the batters in this innings so far. Marnus too gets going with a boundary. Full around off, Labuschagne shuffles across and flicks it with pure timing through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Full delivery on middle, Warner flicks it towards mid-wicket and takes a quick single.
Outside off, David lets it go.
On a good length and outside off, Warner leaves it alone.
Outside off, Marnus does not bother to play at that.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Marnus looks to defend but misses it.
Bowls a bouncer, Labuschagne lets it sail through to the keeper.
Outside off, Marnus offers no shot to this one.
On a good length and outside off, Labuschagne looks to leave but plays at it at the last moment and gets a bottom edge on this one.
Good length delivery on off, Labuschagne blocks it off the back foot.
On a good length on middle, David blocks it well.
Good length delivery on middle, Warner keeps it out.
On a good length on middle, Warner tucks it to mid-wicket.
Outside off, Warner shoulders arms to this one.
On a good length on off, David defends it out.
Good length delivery on off, Warner defends it off the back foot.
On the fourth stump line, Marnus leaves it alone.
Back of a length ball outside off, Labuschagne lets it be but then practices the pull as the ball goes past him.

There is a sound but is it off the ball hitting the edge of the bat or just hitting the surface? Surface feels the umpire and Hot Spot later on confirms that the umpire was indeed correct. Full length delivery outside off, Labuschagne goes for a big drive first up. He is a bit late in his drive. There is a big sound as the ball goes to the keeper. Shaheen Afridi and the keeper go up in a confident appeal. Rizwan thinks they have their man but after a brief discussion skipper Azhar Ali does not take the review. Good decision as Hot Spot later on shows there was no bat involved.
Marnus Labuschagne is the new batsman in.

OUT! Caught! Pakistan draw first blood. Solid comeback from the young Pakistani bowler. He was hit for a boundary in the previous ball. Shaheen hits the deck hard and pulls his length back. It is in the channel of uncertainty around off. Brilliant bowling this from Shaheen. Only one ball nipped back in and that was the first ball that Burns played. He expects this one to come in as well but it does not. Joe looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge as the ball keeps its shape. It goes to the keeper. Rizwan moves to his right and takes a simple catch. Excellent start for the visitors.
FOUR! Burns is off the mark in style. Slightly overpitched around off by Shaheen. Burns gets on his front foot and creams his drive through covers for a boundary. Solid way to get off the mark.
On a good length on off, Burns defends it off the back foot.
Abbas targets the stumps, DW calmly blocks it to get through the over.
Fuller on off, David blocks it off the front foot.

FOUR! Warner and Australia are underway! In a streaky way but Warner won't mind. Good length ball around off, Warner lunges forward to defend but the ball shapes away from him. It takes the outside edge and goes wide of gully and to the fence. Abbas won't mind this.
Abbas gets lucky here. Length ball way outside off, very close to the tramline. David leaves it alone. The umpire feels it is inside the tramline and does not signal a wide.
Good length ball outside off, David is in no hurry and shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball on off, it zips away from the southpaw. Warner reads it well and defends it towards point.
Maiden for Shaheen as well. Fuller on off, Burns pushes it to the left of point. The fielder there dives on that side and saves runs for his side. Watchful start from the hosts.
On the fourth stump line, Joe shoudlers arms to it.
Good length ball on top of off, Burns defends it with a straight bat. First time he has got bat on ball and this will give him some confidence as this has come right off the meat.
Length ball away from the off pole, Burns does not attempt playing that.
Another good ball. Good length ball around off, this one goes away from the right hander. Burns looks to defend but gets beaten again.
Beauty! Shaheen starts with a gem of a delivery. Full outside off, the ball zips back in. Burns goes hard at it first up and looks to drive. The ball cuts him in half on its way to the keeper.
Shaheen Afridi to partner Mohammad Abbas from the other end.
Another consistent line from Abbas to end the over. It is on the fourth stump line. Warner shoulders his arms to this one. Maiden to begin this Test.
Full on off, Warner gets on his front foot and defends it strongly off his front foot.
Good length ball outside off, Warner lets it carry to the keeper.
Length ball outside off, it goes away with the angle. Warner leaves it alone.
Abbas pulls his length back and hits the deck hard around off, Warner hops and defends it towards cover. He calls a loud no to his partner.
Abbas starts with a fuller delivery outside off. Not much movement first up. Warner carefully watches it and leaves it alone.

After a slight delay we are all set to begin. The Pakistan players who were waiting are out on the field.  Australian openers, David Warner and Joe Burns stride out to the middle to open the innings for the hosts. The floodlights are on straightaway. Mohammad Abbas to start the proceedings with the new ball for Pakistan. Two slips and a gully to begin with.

There will be a 10 minute delay. The covers are coming off as we have had some early shower. It is not raining now and let's hope this is the only delay. The groundstaff are roping out the outfield and trying to make the outfield as dry as they can.

Pakistan (Playing XI) - Shan Masood, Imam-ul-Haq (IN for Haris Sohail), Azhar Ali (C), Asad Shafiq, Babar Azam, Iftikhar Ahmed, Mohammad Rizwan (WK), Yasir Shah, Shaheen Afridi, Muhammad Musa (DEBUT) (IN for Naseem Shah), Mohammad Abbas (IN for Imran Khan Jr.).
AUSTRALIA (PLAYING XI)(UNCHANGED) - David Warner, Joe Burns, Marnus Labuschagne, Steven Smith, Travis Head, Matthew Wade, Tim Paine (WK/C), Pat Cummins, Mitchell Starc, Nathan Lyon, Josh Hazlewood.
Toss - Up goes the coin and it comes down in the favour of the hosts. Australia OPT TO BAT!

Hello and welcome to the coverage of the second Test between Australia and Pakistan. It is a Day/Night Test and the hosts have a perfect record in this form of the longest format of the game. Tim Paine and co. would look to make it 6 wins out of 6 and complete a whitewash. Pakistan, on the other hand, are on a 13 game losing streak against Australia in Australia. A few changes are expected to ring in for this game with the confirmed news of Mohammad Abbas being slotted back in. Skipper, Azhar Ali has confirmed that he will bat at number 3. The question is who is going to open? Can Pakistan rise from the ashes and level the series or will Australia make it 14 wins against the touring nation? Stay tuned as the toss is not far  away.

Another unpredictable call from Tim Paine. Many expected him not to enforce follow-on but he has decided to enforce it. The Australian players are waiting near the ropes with  their skipper, Tim Paine having a final word with his troops before they take on the field. Shan Masood and Imam-ul-Haq stride out to open the innings for Pakistan.

The Aussies were not as good as they were on Day 2. They were poor in the field and their bowling lacked the intensity. Starc was the pick of the bowlers picking up 6 wickets. Cummins had 3 to his name whereas Hazlewood had 1. The spinners were unable to pick up a wicket.

What a fight from the tourists. Everyone expected the visitors' innings to be a one session affair at best if not an hour's affair. But Babar Azam and Yasir Shah had other ideas. The duo started the day with the score reading 96/6. The pair added a further 98 runs to take them to 194. Babar fell agonizingly close of 100. But Yasir and Abbas continued to torture the Aussies and added a further 87. Yasir Shah converted his maiden fifty into a hundred taking Pakistan's total to a respectable 302.
By the way, Australia have enforced the follow-on. A very bold call from them. Not many would've thought that after conceding over 300, they will enforce the follow-on. But they have.

Yasir Shah says he is happy to get his first hundred and tells that Babar helped him a lot. On what his thought was when he was on 99, Yasir says that there were a lot of thoughts but he was not taking the pressure.

Yasir Shah, the hero of Pakistan's innings walks off to a huge applause from the crowd. Maiden Test ton and he has shown Pakistan's fight, courage and never give up attitude. The visitors can now at least think of saving this Test. He is caught for a quick chat.

OUT! Caught! Finally the catch goes in the hands. Lyon it is who takes it running forward. A fine catch which means end of a brilliant innings. A short ball on middle, Shah goes for the pull once again but the timing is not proper. It goes high towards deep square leg. Lyon runs forward and pouches it nicely.

Again in the air, again falls safely. The frustration does not seem to end for the hosts. Full ball around off, Musa looks to drive it on the up but gets a leading edge which goes over the mid off region. A single taken.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Uppish but safe again. Short ball on middle. Shah looks to pull but gets a top edge. It goes towards fine leg for a single.

Shout of catch but it is wide of the short leg fielder. It is not not Labuschagne though. Wade has replaced him there. Slightly shortish ball, turning into Musa. He blocks it uppishly which goes right of Wade.
300 up for Pakistan. From 89/6, this is a brilliant recovery from the visitors. Full and outside off, Shah sweeps it towards deep square leg for a single.
Quicker one and outside off, Yasir blocks off the back foot.
Fullish and outside off, Shah drives it towards cover.
Another delivery around off, slightly quicker one. Shah defends it easily.
Around off, Yasir keeps it out.
Runs through the off side now. Full and just outside off, Khan pushes it through point to pick a couple.
Swing and a miss! Good length ball on middle, Musa lines himself up for a massive heave but makes no connection. Few words from Cummins.
FOUR! Wow! Musa in the action now. Pulled away off the front foot. Shortish length ball on middle, Musa stays on the front foot and mows it to deep square leg fence.
On middle, Shah tucks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Bouncer and on middle, Shah ducks it easily.
FOUR! Crashed away! Short ball on middle, Yasir rocks back and hammers it in front of the square leg fence. Brilliant batting. He is seeing the ball like a football it seems.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Outside off and short too. Musa blocks it towards the off side.
Around off, Musa keeps it out.
Shortish one and around off. Musa stays back and defends.
Full and on the pads, Shah flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.

Dropped! Another one from Labuschagne. This is an easier one too. This one pitches around off and turns in. Shah looks to defend but manages an inside edge and onto the pads. It goes straight to Marnus who makes a mess of the easy chance. Lyon cannot believe it.

In the air but it drops in no man's lands. Bouncer and on middle, Shah goes for the pull but manages a top edge. The ball goes high in the air behind towards fine leg. Paine from his position hares to catch but he can't get there. Yasir gets a single.
On middle and leg, Musa tucks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.

FOUR! An edgy one! This is nasty bowling from Cummins. Another short ball on middle, Musa now takes his eyes off the ball as he looks to duck it away. The ball once again catches the handle and flies over the slip cordon and to the third man fence.
Musa Khan walks out at no. 11.

OUT! Abbas has to go. The partnership is broken and Cummins has his second. A peach of a ball this one. Back of a length ball on middle, Abbas looks to duck it away but is in a tangled position. He took off his eyes and the ball takes the gloves and goes straight to gully where the triple centurion pouches it comfortably. 50th Test wicket this year for Cummins.
Shortish length again, this one is around off. Shah just clips it behind square off the back foot to go to the other end.
Back of a length ball down the leg side. Shah looks to pull but misses.
Around off and middle, Abbas this time pushes it back to the bowler.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
On middle, Abbas blocks it nicely.
Around off, Abbas keeps it out.

Appeal for LBW now but the umpire is unmoved. A flighted delivery around off and middle, Abbas comes forward to defend but misses to get hit on the pads. Lyon and the keeper roar out a loud appeal but the umpire is not interested once again.
On the pads, Shah tucks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Shot! Fullish ball on middle and leg, Abbas flicks it deep square leg fence to bag a boundary.

Appeal for a catch but not out says the umpire. Probable came off the thigh pad. Yes, off the thigh pad. Cummins was confident there but not Wade. A length ball on middle and leg, Abbas looks to defend but misses to get hit high on the pads. The ball lobs uppishly and Wade from short leg lunges forward to catch. They appeal but the umpire turns it down and rightly so.
