Another bouncer! But this one is down the leg side. Abbas ducks away easily.
Bouncer now! Abbas ducks it away.
Back of a length ball on middle, Shah tucks it towards fine leg for a run.
Good length ball around off, Shah looks to defend but it goes towards the leg side off the inner half of the bat.
Pat Cummins is back! 19-2-59-1, his numbers so far.
On the pads, Abbas flicks it to square leg.
Tossed up on off, MA once again shows calmness and calmly blocks it.
Floated on off, Abbas keeps it out.
Floated on off, Abbas defends it off the front foot.
On the body, Yasir flick it towards fine leg. There is an easy single available but Abbas and Yasir do yes and no. They finally decide to go for it and they get it with ease.
Spin and bounce on this one. It is short and around the body. Yasir looks to flick but it lobs off his bat onto his body.
Nathan Lyon is back.
DRINKS! Tim Paine is jogging off the field. Looks like it's nature's call that he has to answer. No one can miss that call, right? And the umpire's call for drinks.
Nicely driven! Fullish ball just outside off, Abbas drills the drive through the covers and picks a couple before the fielder can get to the ball.
Full and on off, MA drives it towards cover.
Fuller and outside off, Abbas drives it straight to the mid off fielder.
Length on middle, tucked towards square leg.
Bouncer on middle, Abbas ducks under it.
Good length ball outside off, Shah pushes it towards cover and takes a quick run.
On the pads, flicked towards short mid-wicket.

There it is! Century for Yasir Shah. First one in Tests. What an effort this has been from him. He takes off the helmet and celebrates. Almost every Pakistani player is standing near the ropes. They too jump in joy. He pumps the air and then kisses the ground. What a wonderful moment this is. It would've been end of him though as the shot he played to get there could've easily gone in the hands of the mid on fielder. Good length ball on middle, Shah looks to loft it over mid on but mistimes it. Luckily for him, it lobs over and behind Cummins. He tries to stretch out his arm and get hold of it but he cannot reach there. Yasir is all smiles. He sways his bat and has a huge smile on his face.
The wait continues. Around off, pushed towards cover.
On middle, tucked towards short mid-wicket.
Good length ball on middle, Shah calmly pushes it towards cover. Nervy moments these.
Good length ball on middle, Shah pushes it towards mid on. So he stays on the 99.
Outside off, Abbas leaves it alone.
Full and just outside off, Abbas comes forward and defends it.
Shortish length ball on off, Shah taps it towards short third man and takes a single to move to 99.
Around off, Yasir taps it towards the off side and thinks for a single. He takes off but Abbas sends him back. Could've been very risky.
Length ball on middle, Shah pushes it towards mid on.
Around off, Shah defends it out. He does not seem to be in a hurry.
Full and on off, it is defended
Length around off, Abbas drives it through cover for a run.
Good length ball on middle, Shah tucks it towards mid-wicket for a couple.
Bouncer just outside off, Yasir ducks under it.
Length ball again, driven on the up towards cover.
Good length ball on middle, Shah pushes it towards mid off.
Bouncer on middle, Shah ducks under it. It shoots off after going past the batter on an awkward height for Paine who can't gather it cleanly.

Edged and Four! Through the slip cordon. Full and outside off, Abbas looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and goes through second and third slip. It races to the third man fence. Another frustrating stand this one.
Fullish and on off, Abbas defends it out.
Beaten! Good length ball around off and shaping away. Abbas hangs his bat to defend but misses.

First extra off the innings. Wow, that is some tight bowling from the Aussies. Good length ball on the pads, Shah looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. It goes towards square leg and the batters take a leg bye.
Good length ball just outside off, Shah stays back and taps it off the back foot.
Bouncer down the leg side. Abbas ducks it away.
Fullish and wide outside off, Abbas has no business with it.
Outside off, Abbas leaves it alone.
Flicked nicely but only a run as there is a protection in the deep. Full and on middle, Shah flicks it nicely but straight to deep square leg. So, just a single.
On the pads on a fullish length, Abbas nudges it to fine leg for a single.
Beaten! Good length ball on middle, Abbas comes forward to defend but the ball shapes away to beat the outside edge.
Josh Hazlewood returns to bowl with the second new ball. 11-2-42-1 are his numbers so far.
Around off, Shah defends it out.

Play and a miss! Hold on, Yasir. Do not miss out a golden opportunity. A fuller ball outside off, inviting for the drive. Shah obliges and does so away from the body. He misses to get any bat on ball. Could've been very very risky.
FOUR! Nicely done! Just 6 away from a Test ton, his maiden one. Starc bowls another one on the pads, Shah flicks it to the fine leg fence once again.
Around off and on a good length, Shah comes forward and defends it out.
Now they have opted for it. Second new ball taken.
Full again, Yasir drives it well but straight to mid off.
FOUR! Into the 90s now. Starc starts with a fullish length ball on the pads, Shah flicks it to the fine leg fence.
Second new ball is available now. Australia have not opted to take it yet.
Outside off, Abbas leaves it alone.

In the air... but safe. Gives this one a a lot of air, does Lyon and bowls it just outside off, Shah looks to slog sweep but gets a top edge. The ball goes towards short fine leg. Smith from first slip hares to pouch the ball but he can't get there. He though throws his hand out but can't get it. The ball bounces and hits him on the face. Shah gets a single.
FOUR! Through the covers now! Bowls it full and slightly wide, Shah slams it through covers to bag another boundary.
On off and middle, Shah blocks it out with ease.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Around off, Shah keeps it out.

FOUR! After all the blocking, he decides to smack it over the mid-wicket fence. Flighted ball outside off, Abbas gets it in position and slogs it to the mid-wicket fence. The boundary brings 50-run stand between the two. Useful runs these.
Around off, Abbas comes forward and blocks it out.
Around off and a full, Abbas pushes it back to the bowler.
Slightly quicker, Abbas goes back and blocks it out.
Around off, Abbas keeps it out.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Outside off, Abbas pushes it towards the off side and takes a quick single.
FOUR! Nicely driven! Loopy ball outside off, Abbas drives it down the ground and bags another boundary.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Shout of catch it again but once again it is well short of the long on fielder.
Flighted and around off, Abbas guides it towards third man for a single.

Good delivery this one, pitching around off and turning in. Abbas goes back to defend but misses to get hit on the body. As the ball comes down, it catches the back of the bat and drops near the pads. Could've easily gone to either of the close-in fielders.
On the pads this time, Shah tucks it towards mid-wicket.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Two more! Cry for catch it, but it wide of the mid off fielder. Flighted fullish ball around off, Yasir lofts it uppishly through mid off to pick another couple.
What was that? A high full toss on middle, Shah mistimes it towards mid on.
On the pads this time, Shah this time flicks it behind square to pick another couple.
Shortish length ball outside off, Yasir cuts it through backward point and picks up a couple before the fielder can chase it down and return it to the keeper.
Floated on off, Abbas defends it off the front foot.
Calmly blocks this one after tonking the previous one.

SIX! Hammered away. Hold on, Abbas coming out with a statement with the bat. Floated on middle, Abbas takes the full swing of the bat and smashes it over the long on fence for a biggie. First one of the innings and who would have thought that it would come of Abbas' bat.
Shorter on off, Abbas defends it off the back foot.
Around the pads, Yasir turns it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Short outside off, Shah cuts it uppishly through point for a couple.
Just the single over for Steven Smith and Nathan Lyon is back in business.
Floated on off, MA pushes it to mid off.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Floated on off, Abbas taps it back to the bowler.
On the stumps, Abbas is calm to block it.
Floated on off, Abbas blocks it with a straight bat.
Tossed up on off, Abbas defends it calmly.
Marnus Labuschagne to continue from the other end.
Shorter on off, Shah blocks it.
FOUR! Full toss and Yasir puts it away. It is on middle, Shah goes aerial and hits it over wide long on for a boundary.
Floated on off, Abbas looks to defend but it goes off the outer half of his bat for a single.
Floated on off, Yasir strokes it to the right of the bowler. Smith gets a hand to it but it goes towards mid on. Allowing them to take a single.
Tossed up on off, Shah blocks it off the front foot.

There was a chance of a run out but the throw is at the wrong end. Smith starts with a slightly shorter deliver around off, Shah cuts it to towards point. Travis head dives and stops the ball. Abbas was looking for a single but Yasir send shim back. Travis sends the throw at the keeper's end

Welcome back for the second session on this enthralling Day 3 of this Test. The forecast has been good until now and we hope it remains good for the rest of the day's play. Out walk the Australian players taking their fielding positions. Yasir Shah along with Mohammad Abbas stroll out to the middle to resume Pakistan's fightback. Surprise,surprise! Steven Smith to have a roll of arm after the break.
... Day 3, Session 2 ...

A good fighting session from Pakistan. Probably the first session where they will be happy with their efforts. Yasir Shah and Babar Azam fought out with both the batters getting to their respective fifties. The duo added 105-run stand before Babar Azam fell agonizingly short of his ton. The Aussies were not at their best in this session. Catches did not carry and Labuschagne was guilty of putting down an easy chance of Yasir Shah. Starc's double-wicket over though saw Australia get their Mojo back. Pakistan still trail by a massive 376 runs but Yasir Shah is continuing his battle. How long can the battle last? Join us after the break to find out.

Mitchell Starc is caught down for a quick chat before he heads in for his break. On being asked whether he feels they missed some chances in the session, Starc admits they missed a few chances but credits the team as they managed to take it towards the end. On what was going through his mind during the hat-trick ball, Starc smiles and says nerves.
Ohh! Flighted on off, Abbas looks to defend but the ball turns in and takes the inner half of his bat. It lobs to the right of short leg who was wrong-footed. That will be Tea on Day 3.
Tosses it up very full, too full to trouble Abbas. He manages to defend it onto the ground.
Short outside off, Yasir hops and punches it towards cover for one.
Tossed up on off, Yasir defends it calmly.
Shorter on off, Shah defends it with a straight bat.
FOUR! SHOT! Flighted outside off, Yasir slaps it through covers for a boundary.
Tossed up on off, Abbas pushes it off the outer half of his bat towards cover.
Leg break delivery on off, Abbas gets behind the ball and blocks it.
Floated on off, Abbas defends it with a dead bat.
Leg spinner outside off, Abbas has no interest in playing that.
Tossed up outside off, Abbas leaves it alone.
Flighted on off, Abbas defends it off the front foot.
Marnus Labuschagne comes back on.
Full and outside off, Shah drives it straight to covers.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries. Yasir comes down the track and pulls this tossed up ball through mid-wicket. The ball races to the fence despite there being a man in the deep.
FOUR! Yasir brings out the sweep. He slogs this tossed up one on middle from Lyon through mid-wicket for a boundary. Yasir continues to stage a lone battle against the Aussies.
Tossed up on off, Blocked to the off  side.
Tossed up on off, defended from within the crease by Shah.
Tossed up on off, Shah looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
No run.
Bouncer! Abbas ducks under it.
Beautiful. Full and angling in. Abbas looks to defend but misses. It just about misses the outside edge of the bat.
Around off, Abbas defends it inside the line of the delivery.
On the fourth stump line, Abbas lets it carry to the keeper.
Good length ball around off, Abbas looks to defend it with soft hands but gets a leading edge. It goes to the vacant area at point.
Floats one on off, Shah pushes it to cover.
Slightly short, Yasir defends it off his back foot this time.
Gives this one air, Shah blocks it.
Gives this a lot of air around off. Yasir looks to drive but it goes off the upper half of his bat towards mid off.
Floated on off, Yasir gets on the front foot and blocks it.
Tossed up on off, Yasir defends it onto the ground.
Fuller on the stumps, Abbas keeps it out.
Back of a length on off, Shaha plays it on the off side and gets to the other end.
Fuller on middle, Yasir pushes it to mid on.
Edged but safe. Back of a length ball on off, Yasir looks to play it on the up but it goes off the outer half of his bat towards deep point for a couple.
Once again Yasir looks to defend but then pulls his bat back in.
Oh! Hits the deck hard outside off, Shah looks to defend but gets beaten.
Gives this one air, MA is good with his defenses.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Shorter on off, Abbas gets behind it and defends it onto the ground.
Tossed up on off, MA defends it off the front foot.
Floated on off, Abbas keeps it out.

FIFTY FOR YASIR SHAH! His maiden in Tests. He has played with a lot of resilience and showed the top order how to bat in these conditions. He raises his bat as his teammates applaud his knock. Flighted delivery on off, Yasir strokes it to mid off and gets to his milestone.
Outside off, Abbas shoulders arms to this.
Play and a miss. Good length delivery outside off, Abbas looks to defend but gets squared up.
On the pads, Shah flicks it to the fine leg region for a single.

EDGED BUT SAFE! Just inches away from getting a hat-trick Starc! Brilliant bowling. Full and around middle, swinging in from around the wicket, Abbas looks to flick but the ball takes the leading edge. Goes uppishly but it is wide of point. A single taken.
Mohammad Abbas walks out to face the hat-trick ball from Starc.

OUT! LBW! It looked plumb and it was indeed plumb. Two wickets in two balls for Starc! Very full and swinging in from middle and off. Shaheen looks to flick but misses. It hits him flush on the pads. There is a huge appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Shaheen has a word with his partner and then signals the 'T'. Replay rolls in and first Hot Spot confirms no involvement of the bat. Hawk Eye then comes in and it shows all red. Shaheen has to walk back. Starc on a hat-trick now.
Review time! Afridi is the man in question here. He has been adjudged LBW by the on-field umpire. Starc is fine with the foot. The impact and the pitching also look good.
Shaheen Afridi is the new man in.

OUT! Caught behind! Such a painful blow for Babar and the whole of Pakistan. A brilliant innings from Babar comes to an end just 3 run short of a well-deserved century. Starc gets a 5-fer instead. He has been excellent with the strawberry. The Australian players and fans are ecstatic. Full and on the fourth stump line. Babar looks to go for a drive. He gets a thick outside edge which goes to the right of the keeper. Tim Paine dives on that side and takes a good single-handed catch.
Mitchell Starc is back on.
Floated on middle, Shah strokes it to mid on.
Short on off, Yasir keeps it out.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Tossed up on off, Shah blocks it.
On the pads, Shah works it down the leg side.
FOUR! Poor ball from Lyon. Drag down from Nathan. Yasir gets on his back foot and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Lyon is back.
Short on off, Labuschagne pulls it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Floated on off, once again Shah pushes it to cover.
Tossed up on off, Yasir defends it off the front foot.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
DROPPED! Floated on middle, Shah looks to drive but gets a leading edge. It lobs straight back at Labuschagne and somehow he bottles to take it.
Shorter on off, Azamcuts it through point for a single. That brings up the 100-run stand between the duo.
Change of ends for Marnus Labuschagne.

FOUR! Full and outside off, Shah flat bats it through point. The ball races to the fence for a boundary. This partnership is really frustrating the Aussies here. The wickets are not coming and the runs are also flowing.
Length and around off, driven to covers by Shah.
Full and on leg, Shah flicks it to fine leg for a run.
Length and on off, Shah defends it to the off side.
Azam presents the straightest of the bat and strokes this fuller one down the ground. The batsmen take three runs till the ball gets cleaned up at long off.
Full and around off, driven straight to cover.
Mitchell Starc returns into the attack. 17-5-36-4, his figures so far!
Full and on the pads, Azam flicks it through mid-wicket for a run.
Azam punches this tossed up ball through covers and gets two.
Shah works this fuller one off his pads to mid-wicket for a run.
Tossed up on off, driven to covers.
Tossed up on off, Shah drives this crisply through mid on. The spirited effort by the fielder there saves a certain few runs for the team.
Tossed up on off, Shah defends it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries there. This time Azam pulls it through mid-wicket and gets a boundary.
FOUR! Full and on off, Azam strokes it through mid on. The ball hares towards the fence in a flash.
Outside off, left alone.
Tossed up outside off, defended to the off side.
BEATEN! Marnus gives this one more air and beats the forwards prod of Azam.
Tossed up around off, Azam looks to defend it but gets it off the splice of the bat past the diving slip fielder. The ball goes towards third man and the batsmen take a couple.
Floated around off, Shah blocks it. Maiden from Nathan.
Shorter on off, Yasir defends it off the back foot this time.
Tossed up on off, YS defends it off the front foot towards mid on.
Short around off, Yasir cuts it but Head at backward point dives and saves runs for his side.
Tossed up around off, Yasir defends it off the front foot.
Floated on off, Yasir taps it back to the bowler.
Short and wide outside off, Azam cuts it through point for a couple.
Tossed up and way outside off, Azam is not interested to play it.
Azam plays the short arm pull on this flatter one but drags it to mid on.
Yasir cuts this flatter one outside off through point for a run.
Flighted on middle, Babar flicks it towards long on for a run.
Tossed up outside off, blocks to the off side.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
On off, defended by YS.
Shorter on off, Shah blocks it off the back foot.
On the stumps, defended by Yasir.

STUMPING CHANCE MISSED! Yasir and Babar starting to ride their luck here. Flighted off spinner outside off, Yasir comes down the track and looks to whip it away. The ball spins more than he anticipates and goes right through the bat and pad. It goes to the left of Paine with some extra bounce. The Australian Test skipper fails to collect it. Yasir had no chance of coming back as he was half way down the track. Luck evading Australia at the moment.
Floated around the pads, Azam flicks it to the on side for a single.
Tossed up and outside off, Shah lets the ball go through to the keeper as he watches it closely.
Flighted one around off, Shah defends it to backward point.
Tossed up on off, Shah defends it to short cover.
Another flatter one outside off, Azam cuts it through point for a single.
Flatter and outside off, Shah slaps it through cover-point for a run.
Leg spinner outside off, Shah drives it to covers.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Floated on off, Azam keeps it out.
This time Babar blocks it thoroughly.

Another one which does not carry to the fielder.  Lyon gives this air on off, Azam looks to defend but the ball turns in taking the inside edge of the bat and lobbing off his pad. It goes to the left of the man at short leg. Labuschagne there moves and dives but it is still wide of him.
Floated on off, Azam pushes it to mid off.
Tossed up on off, Azam comes down the track and blocks it.
Flighted around off, Babar plays it to point and keeps the strike.
Floated on off, Azam defends it.
Floated on middle, Yasir strokes it through mid on for one.
Shorter on off, Shah punches it off the back foot.

SAFE! On the bounce. Floated on off, Yasir looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge. The ball falls before it goes to slip. Smith gets forward and takes it. The Australian players start celebrating but Smith indicates that he is unsure whether it is a clean catch or not. The umpires have a word and then take it upstairs with the soft signal as Not Out. Replay rolls in and the T.V. umpire confirms that it is indeed not a clean catch. Smith was standing well behind had he been standing a bit closer then one would feel he could have caught it.
Has Smith caught it cleanly? The soft signal is NOT OUT! It looks a close call. It looked to be taken on the bounce to the naked eye.
Floated leg spinner outside off, Yasir leaves it alone.

DRINKS! We are done with the first hour. Pakistan have been superb with the fightback. Babar Azam  after reaching his fifty has looked solid and Yasir Shah is superb in giving him good company. The Australian bowler's have dished out everything in their kitty but the two Pakistan batsmen have been full of confidence and determination. An interesting passage of play awaits us.
Darted on the pads, Shah flicks it with ease and gets a single.
Floated on off, Shah pushes it to mid off.
Tossed up on off, YS blocks it.
Floated on off, Yasir defends it off the front foot.
On the pads, Shah flicks it to square leg.
Comes around the wicket and tosses it up on off. Yasir taps it back to the bowler.
Slightly slower on off, Azam pushes it to cover.
Floated on off, Azam strokes it to point.
Gives this one air on off, BA gets on his front foot and defends it onto the ground.
Short again from Marnus. Yasir pulls it against the turn for a single.
Short and spinning away, Azam plays it with the spin and cuts it away towards point for one.
Flighted leg spinner on off from Labuschagne to begin with. Babar calmly blocks it.
Marnus Labuschagne is on now.
On the stumps, YS blocks it to get through the over.
Off spinner around the pads, Babar turns it with the spin towards square leg for one.
Tossed up on off, Babar pushes it to mid off.
Good shot but straight to the fielder. Tossed up on off, Babar drives it right off the middle but straight to short cover.
Floated on off, Yasir strokes it to the right of the bowler. Lyon dives but fails to stop the ball. It goes towards long on for one.
Slightly shorter outside off, Yasir punches it to cover.
Follows the boundary with a solid back foot defense.

FOUR! Uppish but away for four! Looked like it was a plan to send one full ball after some short stuff. Little too straight from Cummins. It is around the pads, Babar gets on his back foot and then flicks it uppishly wide of mid-wicket for a boundary.
Bouncer! Azam sees it and ducks under it.
Back of a length around the body, Yasir hops and tucks it to the on side for one.
Around the pads once again, Babar glances it to the leg side for one.
Good length ball on the pads, Babar flicks it towards fine leg and gets a couple.
The batsman works it down the leg side.
On the pads, worked towards the leg side for a single.
Floated outside off again, Yasir gets down on one knee and drives this one through the cover region for a single.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Floated on off, Yasir pushes this one towards the man at cover.
Drags one back does Lyon, Azam goes deep in his crease and works it towards wide mid on for a single.
Shah once again looks to go for the flick on this fuller one on the pads but gets and inside edge on to his pads. The ball roll to the leg side.
Full and on the pads, Shah flicks it to mid-wicket.
BOUNCER! Short ball around middle, Shah ducks under it.
Good length and around off, Azam punches the ball off the back foot to the off side and takes a single.
Length and around off, Azam drives it through covers and takes a comfortable two. With this 50-run stand also comes up between the two.

OHHH! Yes, no, yes. Not good from Pakistan's point of view. Shah blocks this length ball to the offside Babar calls for a single. Intially Shah does not start but then takes off. The fielder at covers pounces on the ball and has a shy at the bowler's end. Yasir was well miles outside the crease when the ball went past the stumps. Had the fielder hit it, Shah would have been a gonner.

Just short! What a beauty by Lyon! Floated delivery on off, the ball turns back in after pitching. Yasir Shah looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and goes towards first slip but falls just short of Steven Smith there as he dives forward. Close calls here!
On off, driven towards the man at cover.
Floated on off again, it spins back in. Shah gets behind the line of the delivery.
Tossed up on off, defended by the batter.
Floated outside off, Yasir goes for a wild slog sweep towards mid-wicket but completely misses the ball.
Tossed up around off, Shah blocks it solidly off the front foot.
Bouncer down the leg side, Azam lets it be.
Length and on off, Babar drives this to mid on off the full face of the bat.
Brilliantly driven but excellently fielded. Babar drives this length ball through covers. Marnus fielding there puts in a dive and saves a certain boundary for his team.
Outside off, solidly blocked off the front foot.
Short one down the leg side, Babar  lets it go through by ducking under it.
Length and around off, Azam defends it to the off side.
Tossed up outside off, Shah goes for a booming drive through the off side but gets a thick outside edge. The ball goes past the point fielder towards third man. The batsmen take a couple.
Full and on the pads, Yasir flicks it to mid-wicket.
Given this one more air. Shah drives it but finds mid off.
Flighted around off, blocked solidly.
Flatter and around middle, Azam works it towards mid-wicket for a run.
Tossed up on off, Babar defends it back to the bowler.
Length and outside off, Shah hops inside the crease and defends it to the off  side.
Length and around off and middle, Shah strokes it to mid on..
Bowls this oen down the leg side.Yasir looks to turn it away from his hip but misses.
Fuller on off, Yasir drives it to mid on.
Good length ball on off, Azam strokes it to point.
Length ball on off, Azam punches it to cover.
Floated on off, YS defends it off his back foot.

FOUR! Nicely played. Flighted around off, Shah gets on his front foot and drives it through extra cover. Starc moves to his left from mid off and tries to stop it with a dive but fails to do so as the ball goes through him.
Gives this one air on off, Yasir gets on his front foot and looks to defend but the ball spins in a lot more. It goes wide of the man at short leg as it goes off the inner half of his bat.
Tossed up on off, Yasir keeps it out.
Shorter off spinner around off. Babar waits for it and punches it through backward point. The fielder cleans it up before the ropes saving a run for his side.
Lyon starts with a typical off spinner on off. Babar gets on his back foot and punches it to mid on.
Nathan Lyon comes to bowl for the first time in this Test.
Good length ball just outside off, Yasir looks to defend but misses.

Beautifully bowled. Finally some real movement in the day. Fuller outside off, the ball swings in late. Tim Paine looks to collect it behind but there is further movement as the ball goes towards him. He fails to collect it and the ball deflects after hitting his finger. Does not cost any run.
Back of a length ball on off, Yasir hops and defends it with a slant bat. Good show of resilience so far from Yasir.
Good length ball on off, Yasir looks to drive but he checks his drive. It goes off the inner half of his bat towards mid on.
Length ball on off, YS defends it.
Cummins starts with a good length ball on off. Babar transfers his weight on his back foot and punches it to the left of cover and calls for one straightaway.
Pat Cummins comes on to bowl replacing Josh Hazlewood. His figures so far read 14-1-46-1.
Another good ball to end the over. Yorker on off, Shah does really well to jam it out.

EDGED AND FOUR! If there was a third slip Yasir would have been marching towards the pavilion. Good length ball around off, Yasir goes for the big drive. The ball moves away and takes a fat outside edge of Yasir's bat. It goes right between Smith and Warner at second slip and gully and to the fence.
Beauty! Gem of a ball from Starc. He hits the deck hard around off, it comes back in after pitching. Yasir looks to defend but misses.
Good length ball on off, Babar punches it off his back foot towards cover for one.
Around off, Azam pushes this to mid off.
Fuller on middle, Babar pushes it to mid on.
Full again this is also around off, Yasir squeezes it through covers and gets a couple.
Fuller on off, Yasir pushes it to cover.
Solid. Fuller on off, Yasir blocks it with a dead bat.
Good length ball on off, Shah punches it off his back foot.
Length ball around off, Yasir looks to punch it on the up but ends up chopping it off the lower half of his bat towards slip.
Short ball on off, Babar pulls it to fine leg for one.

Appeal for LBW! Umpire shakes his head. Starc bowls one on a length and around off, The ball swings in and hits Yasir on the thigh pad beating his defensive push. The Aussies appeal but Starc is not interested and they abort it halfway. May be going over the stumps there.
Beauty from Starc! he keeps one on a length and in that channel of doubt. Shah goes for a push off the back foot. He fails to get to the pitch of the ball as it goes past the outside edge.
Length and around off, Shah looks to defend it to the off side but gets an inside  edge to the leg side.
Snorter from Starc. he bowls one short and around off, Shah does well to sway away from the line.
Length and around off, Shah drives it off the front foot through the covers. But lack of timing means that the ball fails to cross the boundary ropes. The batsmen are content with a couple.
Shah looks to defend this length ball to the off side but the ball just about swings to take the outside edge and go all along the ground to the off side. Shah almost got squared up there.

FOUR! FIFTY FOR BABAR AZAM! His 12th in Tests. This series has been a calling of Babar Azam, the Test match batsman. He gets to his milestone in style as well. On the pads, Azam uses his wrist and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary. In a tough circumstance he has been excellent. He raises his bat as everyone applaud his knock. Babar knows the job is nowhere near done and he needs to convert this into a big hundred.
Length and around middle and leg, Yasir looks to flick it to the leg side but gets an inside edge on his pads. The ball goes towards mid-wicket and the batsmen take a single.
FOUR! Fantastically played. Josh goes short but the ball doesn't rise much. It sits perfectly for Shah to hook it through mid-wicket for boundary.
Length ball on off, Yasir defends it to the off side.
Full and on middle, Shah drives it straight to mid on.
Back of a length and around middle and leg, Shah looks to tuck it towards the leg side  but gets beaten. The ball raps him on the thigh pads.
Length and around off, Shah drives it through point for a run.
Good length ball outside off. Yasir shows very good discipline and leaves it alone.
Short ball around middle and leg. Yasir hops and strokes it towards point.
Fuller on off. This is bowled at around 143 kph. Yasir defends it off the upper half of his bat.
This one is way outside off, Yasir does not disturb that.
Ohh! Good length ball outside off, it goes with the angle but straightens a tad after pitching. Yasir looks to drive it straight but the ball goes past the outside edge.
Back of a length ball around the body. Yasir hops and tucks it to the on side and keeps the strike. Just a single off Hazlewood's first over of the day.
Bangs one in short. Yasir Shah takes his eyes off it and ducks under it.
Slightly fuller and outside off, Yasir drives it straight to short cover.
On the fourth stump line, Yasir calmly shoulders arms to it.
Goes wide of the off pole, tempting Yasir to go for it. Shah though is not interested.
Hazlewood starts with a good length ball on off, Yasir defends it with a dead bat.
Josh Hazlewood to start from the other end.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! First one of the day! Fuller on off and middle, Babar gets behind the ball and drives it gorgeously through mid on for a boundary. Moves to 48 with that.
Good length ball on off,  Babar plays it to point and calls a loud no to his partner.
On the pads, Yasir turns it towards fine leg and scores his first run of the day.
Starc corrects his line and bowls it on off. Yasir defends it off the back foot.
Down the leg side. Yasir looks to flick but the ball goes off his thigh pad to the left of the keeper. Tim Paine does well diving on that side as the ball bounces just in front of him.
Babar off the mark for the day straightaway. Starc starts the day with a length ball around the pads, Azam tucks it towards square leg and gets a single.

We are all set to begin Day 3! The Australian players are out on the field led by their skipper Tim Paine. Overnight batting pair of Babar Azam and Yasir Shah stride out to resume their innings. Mitchell Starc to start the proceedings for the day.

Trail - A massive 493. Wickets in hand - Just 4. Pakistan are staring down at an inevitable follow-on. At this point they can hope for some respectability to the score and for that to happen they need Babar Azam to play another gem. The other thing the visitors would be hoping for is rain. As much as possible so that they can think of saving this Test. But if there's any side who can be absolutely shambolic one day and completely unbeatable the next then it's Pakistan. Australia, on the other hand, will look to continue what they have been doing in this game so far. They'd look to bundle out the tourists as quickly as possible and then either make them bat again or opt otherwise. The weather forecast for the day is not too good. What's in store for us on this all important Day 3 of the second Test?
... Day 3, First Session ...

So Day 1 belonged to Australia, Day 2 belonged to Australia. Is it going to be the same on Day 3? By the looks of it anything else would be a surprise. The weather forecast for the day is not too good but let's hope that does not hold true. It is another early start, so join us at 1330 Local (0300 GMT) for the start of Day 3. Till then, cheers!

Another disappointing and disheartening day for Pakistan. They were outplayed, outclassed and humiliated by the hosts. First with the bat and then later on with the ball. After being on the field for almost 5 sessions, the tourists would have wanted their openers to fight it out but it was a total capitulation. Only one recognized batsman, Babar Azam is out in the middle along with Yasir Shah. Only a miracle can see them even avoid a follow-on from here on.

The day started off for the Aussies with Labuschagne and Warner continuing their good work. Labuschagne's 162 and David Warner's memorable and historic unbeaten 335 saw Australia declare for a giant score of 589. Then, the hosts continued their good work with the ball from the previous Test. as the pace trio of Starc, Cummins and Hazlewood wrecked havoc with the strawberry. Cummins and Hazlewood got one wicket each while Starc was bowling poison and his 4-wicket haul ensured that Australia enter Pakistan's tail.

Terrific, terrific day for Australia. A 10/10 day for the hosts. The hero of the day, David Warner gets congratulated by all his teammates and he leads them off the field. It was his day/evening and he has the second highest individual score in Tests for Australia. He bows down to the crowd as they give him a huge applause.
Full delivery on middle, Yasir defends it out. It is STUMPS ON DAY 2.
Back of a length ball outside off, Yasir guides it through gully for another couple. Warner hares after it and cleans it up.
Full delivery on middle, Shah plays it through mid on and picks up an easy couple.
BEATEN! Beautiful bowling from Cummins! Bowls it on a length outside off, Yasir looks to defend it but fails to get any bat on it.

We are approaching that time of the evening when one would believe that a night watchman is better suited to facing majority of the balls. Protect Babar tonight and unleash him tomorrow afternoon. Having said that, will the tail be able to handle the swing of the New South Wales trio (Starc, Cummins, Hazlewood)? Pakistan would be simply hoping that this period gets seen off quickly. Remember, Yasir Shah has already shown us twice in this series that he is no mug with the bat.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Babar tucks it to mid-wicket and picks up a single.
Full delivery on off, Babar defends it out.
Yasir is not learning! He goes after a wide one again but luckily for him, there is no edge this time too. End of another excellent over by Starc.
Full and wide outside off, Yasir goes after it but is beaten. He hasn't learnt from the previous batters. He should not be chasing such balls.
Back of a length and on off, Yasir defends it awkwardly. It seemed like he lost sight of that delivery.
Back of a length and on off, this is guided to point.
Angled into the batter, it is worked to mid-wicket.

NOT OUT! Nothing on Snicko as it passes the bat. Australia have lost both their reviews now. This is short and down the leg side, Yasir looks to flick but misses. Paine catches the ball and appeals but the umpire shakes his head. Tim reviews after a chat with Starc. Replays roll in and they show nothing.
Have Australia got another? A appeal for a caught behind has been taken upstairs. Paine is pretty confident.
No he cannot. Back of a length on off, Babar defends it off his back foot and shouts a loud no to his partner.
Length ball on off, Azam defends it off his back foot. Will Babar be able to take a single of the last ball?
Beauty! Gem of a ball from Cummins. Even the umpire got excited. Good length ball which looks to come in with the angle. It zips away off the deck. Babar looks to defend but gets squared up.
Good shot and also good fielding. Fuller outside off, Babar plays one of his classic cover drives. Labuschagne at short cover does well to stop it to his left.
Attacks the middle pole, Babar defends it with a dead bat.
Fuller on middle, Babar turns it away to fine leg and gets a couple.
Good length and on off, defended. End of an over with two wickets in it. Australia or Starc I should say, all over Pakistan at the moment.
Australia are into the tail. Yasir Shah is the new man in. This could be a 150 kph ball. Watch out, Yasira....

OUT! Another one bites the dust! Once again it is an unbelievable shot from the batter. What are the Pakistan batters doing? They are nearing Stumps and such outrageous shots are being played. Azam will be gutted watching all this from the other end. Starc gets his 4th and it is his second in the same over. It is another nothing delivery, full and wide outside off. Rizwan reaches out for it. The ball goes off the outside edge and it is an easier catch for Paine this time. With around 10 overs to go tonight, we might well see Pakistan being bowled out.
BEATEN! This lands on off and then it slants away. Rizwan looks to play it but the ball beats the outside edge.
Almost! This is a length ball outside off, Rizwan plays away from his body, he gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Mohammad Rizwan walks out to bat.

OUT! That is a rippa! Tim Paine, you beauty! But this is a horrendous shot from Ahmed. He did try one similar early on, that time he got beaten but this time the ball finds the edge and it is taken. Starc gets his third and Pakistan have half their side back in the hut before they cross 100. This is a short and wide delivery outside off, Iftikhar throws his bat at it but the ball goes off the outside edge and it is going towards first slip. Paine dives full stretch to his right, sticks one hand out and the ball stays in. Had he missed it, no one would have been able to take the rebound. Joe Burns at first slip had his back turned while the second slip fielder was taking evasive action. The Aussies are absolutely ecstatic. Can they get into the tail tonight?
Good length and on off, it is defended.
Length and on off, Azam looks to defend it but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
BOUNCER! Azam is happy to duck under it.

Unless the players are interested in signing autographs or clicking selfies, hard to understand so many boundary riders. Fine leg, deep square leg, sweeper cover - why? Just because Babar Azam is a terrific driver of the cricket ball? You have batted the best of 5 sessions, so let's face it - you cannot lose from here, can you? Even if you do, it is too early to think about that! Who cares about the runs at this stage of the day? Get all the boundary riders in, pack the slip cordon and if in this process, a few boundaries go by, let them go! But with this field, hard to see a wicket coming off a good ball.
Length and outside off,  Azam drives it through covers but gets it off the outside half off the bat to point. A couple taken.
Length and down the leg side, Babar tries to flick it but misses it.

Good stop in the field. Labuschagne makes his presence felt on the ground. Azam plays a free flowing drive through covers on this length ball outside off. Marnus there dives to his right and stops it.
Length and around off, played to mid off.
Length and around off, defended to the off side  from within the crease
Back of a length on middle, Babar taps it to point and crosses to the other end.
Full and around off, Azam taps it to gully.
On a length and outside off, Ahmed taps it to point and hares for a quick run.

We are approaching the last half an hour of the day's play. I mean, the officially allotted last 30 minutes. Pakistan need both these batsmen to stay till the close. At least, Babar. Australia, will be thinking, as they always do, get one in this passage and then as the saying goes, one gets two, have Pakistan 6 down at Stumps.
Back of a length and outside off, Azam drives it through covers for a single.
Full and on off, Azam drives it straight to mid off.
Good, solid defense to end the over. Fuller around off, IA gets on his front foot and keeps it out.
Fuller on off, Iftikhar does well to defend it with a straight bat.
Pat goes outside off and Iftikhar does not go chasing after it.
Cummins maintains his length and bowls it closer to off. Iftikhar looks to hit it straight but sends it back to Pat off the bottom half of his bat.

FOUR! In the air but safe! Good length ball outside off, Iftikhar drives it on the up. He does not time it well and also hits it uppishly. Luckily it is in the gap through covers and has the legs to reach the fence.
Good length ball on off, Iftikhar pushes it to mid off.
Pat Cummins is back on! 10-1-32-1, his numbers so far.
Back of a length on off, Iftikhar punches it to the off side and keeps the strike with a single.
Now Iftikhar has a flash at it but luckily misses. Good length ball on the fourth stump line. Iftikhar falls into the trap and goes for the drive but misses.
Length ball on off, Iftikhar defends it towards cover.
This one is closer to the off pole but Iftikhar once again does not flirt with it.
Good length ball way outside off, Ahmed does not tease it.
Starc attacks the stumps, Iftikhar pushes it to mid off.
Good length ball on off, Babar defends it towards the leg side. His bottom hand comes off the grip as he blocks it.
Bouncer! Josh tests Babar with another short one. Azam sits under it.
Fuller on off, Azam this time gets on his front foot and blocks it. Playing some textbook defense is Babar.
Back of a length on off, Babar gets on his back foot and defends it classically.
Good running! Length ball on off, Babar dabs it towards backward point and calls for two straightaway. Iftikhar responds and they get the second with ease.

Not quite sure with this field set for Babar Azam. They have a slip for him, a straightish mid on and a gully. Babar is a guy who loves to drive and hence, a couple of slips are mandatory. Even though he looks set, but under the lights and with the Aussie bowlers hungry, Paine might set up some fodder for his lions.
Bouncer around the body but down the leg side. Babar ducks under it.
Edged but short again! This is on off, it angles away. Ahmed looks to defend it off the back foot but it goes off the outside edge and lands well short of second slip.

Outrageous shot that! Not sure why Ahmed played that. Yes, he is an attacking batsman but that was atrocious. Short and way too wide. Ahmed tries to reach out but misses it. Had he been dismissed in that manner, he would have kicked himself.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Played to the point region by the batsman.
Good length and on off, Azam stays back and keeps it out.
Back of a length and around off, Azam guides it towards point and gets to the other end.
A short one and on off, evaded.

FOUR! A top shot to get off the mark! This is not a full delivery, it is outside off. Ahmed creams it through covers, on the up and it races away to the fence. This shot should give him good confidence. Not easy playing on the up.

Three runs! Another good shot on the up! A length delivery angling into the batter, Azam strokes it uppishly but well wide of the bowler. Mid on gives it a chase. The ball slows down as it gets to the ropes and three runs are taken.
Back of a length and on off, BA goes back and keeps it out. He is really playing well here but needs support from the other end.
One more short one on middle, Azam lets it go over him.
Length and outside off, it is pushed to covers.
A little too straight, Iftikhar works it to square leg.
Well, not a yorker but a fuller ball outside off, Iftikhar lets it be.
A sharp short one to welcome the new batter. Ahmed ducks under it at the very end. A yorker now coming up?
Iftikhar Ahmed walks out to bat. Pakistan looking in dire straits.

OUT! TAKEN! This time the edge finds the gloves of the keeper! Starc gets his second and the partnership which did get off to a start has been cut short. The angle does him in here. It lands on off which means Shafiq has to play at it but then it slants away. The ball kisses the outside edge and goes to Paine who makes no mistake.

EDGY FOUR! Stroke of luck there for Pakistan. They need a lot more like this. Full and outside off, Asad throws his bat at it. It flies off the outside edge and goes between the third slip and the gully fielder and into the third man fence.
Slightly fuller and on off, Asad strokes it straight to mid off.
Back of a length and on off, Azam stays back and keeps it out.
Shorter and on middle, Azam spots it early and ducks under it.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! This is bread and butter stuff for Azam. On the pads, Azam is very strong, he clips it through mid-wicket and it races away to the fence.
Good length again and on off, defended.
Azam is a little late there! Slightly shorter and outside off, Azam looks to push at it but the ball skids through and he gets beaten.

Drinks Break! Australia continue to put Pakistan under the pump. The visitors continue to have a torrid time and they have lost two wickets in this session. Babar Azam is still out there in the middle and Azhar Ali would hope that him and Asad Shafiq can take them somewhere out of trouble.
Fuller in length and on middle and leg, Shafiq flicks it straight to the man at mid-wicket.
Length and on middle, Shafiq blocks it solidly off the front foot.
On off, Babar pushes it towards cover for one.
Good running! Another length ball on off, Asad taps it towards cover and takes off. The fielder gets to the ball and has a shy at the non-striker's end but misses.
Beauty! Excellent use of the angle there. This is on a length and around off, it slants away. Asad looks to defend but is beaten.
Lands it on a length and around off, it is kept out nicely.
Mitchell Starc is back on! He was good in his first spell and if he can bowl another good spell here, Australia might just get another wicket or two.
Length and around off, Azam punched it off the back foot to the off side.
BOUNCER! Azam ducks under it with ease.
Length and outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Now on the other side of the wicket. Hazlewood delivers one on middle and leg, Azam flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.

FOUR! Handsomely driven. Azam poses for the shutter bugs after this shot. Hazlewood lands it on a length and outside off, Babar leans and drives it through covers. The ball races to the fence in a flash.
Length and around off, Azam taps it back to the bowler off the back foot.

Just short? Maybe! Shorter and around off, Asad looks to defend but there is extra bounce. It goes off the outside edge towards third slip. Wade dives to his right and stops it nicely. Not sure if it carried or not. Even if it did, it would have been a tough chance.
On middle, Asad keeps it out.
Back of a length and around off, Azam plays it late and guides it through backward point for three. Azam is looking really solid.
A short one on off, Azam evades it nicely.
This is angled into the off pole, Azam stays back and keeps it out.
Outside off, not played at.
On the stumps, kept out.
On off, blocked.
The batsman rocks onto the back foot and punches the ball. The batsmen have run through for a single.
FOUR! Crisp! Full and on off, Azam prods forward and milks it to the long off fence.
Another one on off, Azam prods forward and keeps it out.
Good length and on off, kept out.

EDGED AND FOUR! Very lucky for Shafiq. Almost the 4th wicket goes down. Cummins bowls  one around off and on a length, Shafiq looks to defend but gets it off the outside edge towards second slip. But as Asad plays it with soft hands the ball did not carry to Smith and runs through him for a boundary at third man. Shafiq is off the mark in a nervy fashion.
Full and on the pads of Shafiq. He goes for the flick down the leg side but misses it. The ball brushes his pads and goes towards Paine.
Fuller in length and around off, Babar flicks it to mid-wicket and takes a single.
Good length and outside off, Azam taps it to covers.
Length and around off, Babar defends it to the off side.
Good length and outside off, Babar leaves it with ease for the keeper.
Asad Shafiq is the next batsman in.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! No. 3 down. Quality bowling from Hazlewood, he deserves this wicket. He kept bowling that excellent line and length, beat the bat a few times and now finally gets the reward. Bowls it again in the corridor of uncertainty. Masood, with not a lot of foot movement, looks to defend but does so inside the line. The ball hits the outside edge and goes into the mitts of the keeper. Pakistan slip further.
Slightly fuller and around off, Shan blocks it back to the bowler.
Outside off, left alone for the keeper to grab it.
BUMPER! Hazlewood bangs one in the centre of the pitch and Masood ducks it.
On a length and outside off, Masood watches the ball closely as he shoulders arms to it.
Good length and outside off, Masood guides it towards gully where Warner fields and cuts any possibility of a run.
Back of a length and on off, Azam guides it to gully.
This is angled into the pads, it is worked to mid on.
FOUR! Too full again and Cummins pays the price. Very full and outside off, Azam strokes it through covers and it races away to the fence.
Goes fuller and on middle, Azam strokes it back to the bowler.
This time he goes back and defends it out solidly.
Top nut! Not a lot you can do about that. This lands on off and it is on a length. Azam is once again squared up as he tries to defend. Gets beaten.
BEATEN! Slightly outside off, in the corridor of uncertainty. Masood defends inside the line and gets beaten.
Shorter and around off, Masood pokes at it tentatively but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Back of a length and on off, defended.
Fuller in length and on middle, Shan pushes it to mid on.
Good length and on off, Shan defends it out.

In the air... but safe! Shan was caught in two minds here. It is a short one outside off, Masood isn't sure whether to pull it or not. In the end he plays a half pull shot. It goes wide of mid on where the fielder dives and makes a good stop.
Another solid defensive stroke to this ball on the off pole. A dot to end but an excellent over for Pakistan.
Another length delivery and on off, Azam lunges and keeps it out nicely.
That is a beauty! Excellent comeback! This lands on a length and around off, it straightens. Azam is squared up as he tries to defend but gets beaten.

FOUR! Second boundary in the over and this is even better than the last one! Fuller and around off, Azam shows the full face of the bat and creams it past mid off. No chance of stopping that. The skipper needs to play another top knock here.
Good running now! Shorter and on off, Shan taps it towards cover and takes a quick single.
FOUR! Excellent flick shot! Very elegant! Full and on the pads, Masood stands tall and works it through square leg for a boundary.
Another length delivery and outside off, Azam is happy to let that be.
Length ball outside off, Babar shoulders arms to it.
Length and on off, defended off the back foot to the off side.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Masood whips it to square leg and crosses over for a single.
Outside off, left alone by Shan.
Good length ball on middle, Masood works it to the on side and picks up a couple.
Bowling change as well. Josh Hazlewood is into the attack now. Replaces Mitchell Starc.
Change in batting order. Babar Azam has been promoted and walks out at number 4.

OUT! CAUGHT! It is a clean catch from Steven Smith and Azhar Ali has to make the long walk back to the pavilion. This though is brilliant bowling from Pat Cummins. Bowls a full ball on off squaring up Ali, he looks to push at it but it goes off the outside edge to Smith at second slip. He comes forward and takes a good catch. The umpires go upstairs to check whether it is a clean catch. The replays roll in and they show that Smith has taken it cleanly. Pakistan in deep trouble at the Adelaide Oval.

Azhar Ali has been caught at second slip but the umpires have gone up to check whether it is a clean catch or not. The soft signal is OUT! So even if it is 50/50 Azhar will have to walk back. It looks clean and the replay confirms that it is a clean catch.
Full delivery on off, Ali blocks it to cover.
Short ball down the leg side, Masood pulls it to fine leg and takes a single.
Good length ball outside off, Masood lets the ball go to the keeper.
Good length ball on off, Shan guides it to the slip cordon.
Fuller one on middle, Masood pushes it to mid on.
On a length outside off, Azhar shoulders arms to this one.
Very full delivery on off, Ali digs it out to gully.
Fullish ball in the channel outside off, Ali does not fiddle with it and lets the ball go to the keeper.
Good length ball outside off, Azhar lets the ball go to the keeper.
BOUNCER! Starc bowls this down the leg side, Ali ducks under it.
Good length ball on middle, Shan flicks it to square leg and takes a single.
FOUR! Brilliant shot from Azhar! Full delivery down the leg side, Ali flicks it through mid-wicket for the first boundary of the innings.
Cummins goes full on off this time, Ali blocks it out.
Good length ball on middle, Azhar solidly defends this back to the bowler.
Good length ball on off, Azhar defends it to cover.
Another fuller one from Pat Cummins, Masood tucks it to mid-wicket and gives Azhar the strike.
Full ball on off, Shan pushes this towards mid on.
Azhar defends this full delivery on off to cover.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Azhar flicks it to the on side.
Fullish ball by Starc, Masood drives this crisply through mid on and picks up an easy three.
Short delivery on the leg stump line, Masood works it to square leg. Head dives to stop the ball but fails to do so. The batters manage to take a couple.
Fullish delivery on middle and leg, Masood blocks it to mid on.
Back of a length ball on off, Ali guides it to gully where Warner slides and makes a half stop. The ball rolls towards point and the batters take a single.
Fullish ball on middle, Shan pushes it back to Cummins.
Full delivery outside off, Masood pushes it to cover for a couple.
Full delivery outside off, Masood shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on middle, Masood tucks it to square leg for nothing.
On a length outside the off stump line, Shan shoulders his arms to this one.
Bowls a back of a length ball outside off, Masood lets the ball go to the keeper.
Pat Cummins will bowl from the other end. 3-1-3-0 are his figures so far.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Ali is solid in defense.
Good length delivery on the pads, Ali whips it to fine leg and picks up another couple before Pat Cummins can come around and collect the ball.
Full delivery outside off, Azhar Ali drives this through mid off for a couple. Matthew Wade hares after it from mid off and makes a good sliding stop.
Good length ball in the channel outside off, Ali makes another leave to the keeper.
This time goes back of a length does Starc. Azhar shoulders arms to this one.
Starc starts with a fullish delivery outside off, Azhar does not fiddle with it.

We are all set to begin the final session of Day 2. Shan Masood and Azhar Ali make their way out to the middle. The Australian players are also out in the field. Mitchell Starc will start for the hosts with Azhar Ali taking strike.
... Day 2, Session 3 ...

What a session for Australia! What a session for David Warner. It looked like the Aussie would try and go past Brian Lara's world record score of 400 but Tim Paine called his side in when Warner went past Sir Don Bradman's score. With 589 runs on the board and the Pakistani players tired for fielding for a day and a half, Tim Paine would have hoped to get a wicket or two before the break. He did not get two but he certainly got one. Starc bowled fire balls and got rid of Imam before the break. Skipper Azhar Ali and Shan Masood will have a task in hand in the final session as the ball is relatively new and the strawberry has a tendency to move a bit under lights. Can Pakistan fight out the final session of the day with little to no damage or will Australia pile on the misery? Join us after the break to find out.

Huge appeal but the umpire is unmoved. It pitches on middle and leg and goes with the angle. Shan looks to flick but misses. The ball hits him on the pads. The Aussies go up in a huge appeal but the umpire turns it down. Australia have lost a review and they do not take the risk of taking the second review. With that, it is DINNER ON DAY 2.
Very full, almost a yorker. Shan digs it out.
Good length ball outside off, Shan leaves it alone.
Closer to the off pole, Shan blocks it with a dead bat.
On the pads, Masood flicks it to mid-wicket.
Length ball on off, Masood plays it to point.
Slightly shorter around off, Azhar lets it carry to the keeper. Wicket maiden from Starc. He has bowled some real venoms.
149.1 kph ball this. It is outside off, Ali leaves it alone.
Back of a length ball on off, Azhar keeps it out of his back foot.
Azhar Ali, the skipper, is the new batsman in.

OUT! Caught! You just cannot keep David Warner out of this game, can you? Excellent bowling this from Starc. Bowls a real fajita. Hits the deck really hard with a 150.7 kph ball. It is in the channel of uncertainty around off. Imam looks to defend but the ball takes a thick outside edge straight to the man at gully. David Warner there pouches it in safely. The day he has had, one would feel he would have taken it even if it was 4 feet away.
Good leave! It starts on off and comes in. Imam leaves it alone. The ball goes over middle and off.
Oh! Stinger. It is short on the body, Imam looks to defend but it hits him on his glove.
Outside off, Masood has no business with it.
Full around off, Imam pushes it to the right of mid on and gets a single.
Away from the off pole, Imam leaves it alone.
Shan is off the mark. Fuller on off, Shan flicks it towards mid on and calls for a quick run. Imam responds and they get it with ease.
Fuller and just outside off, Masood is aware of his off pole and leaves it alone.
Length ball around the pads, Shan looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the body.
Inswinging length ball around off, Imam shoulders arms and makes away for the ball to go to the keeper.
Bouncer! A vicious one as it is sent out at 147.2 kph. Imam sways away from it.
Good length ball on the pads. This one is bowled at 148 kph. Imam defends it back to the bowler.
This one is a fiery delivery from Starc. Around late 140s outside off, Imam lets it carry to the keeper.
Starc hits the deck hard outside off, Imam leaves it alone.
Shapes in off the surface. It is quick as well.; On a length and coming in, Imam looks to tuck it on the on side but gets a leading edge which falls well short of the man at gully.
A length ball, around middle and leg, Masood looks to defend but the ball pitches and then seams away, beating the outside edge.

Close call. Imam works it through mid-wicket and calls for a quick single. Masood responds but so does Travis Head. He charges onto the ball and has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. Direct hit would have had him!
Full and around middle, hint of inward shape, Imam flicks it off the inner half towards square leg.
Full and around off, pushed towards cover.
Around off, blocked from the crease.

NOT OUT! Pitching outside leg. Excellent decision from the umpire. On a good length, around leg (to the naked eye), Imam was on his back foot as he looked to flick. Cummins roared an appeal for LBW as soon as that hit the pads but the umpire was firm. There was a long discussion between Paine and Cummins and with 5 seconds left on the clock, the signal goes up for the review. No inside edge mark on Hot Spot but Ball Tracker shows it to be pitching outside leg. Well, both openers survive but straightaway, Australian new-ball bowlers are showing the length to be bowled on this track.

This time it is Australia who have taken the review. 'This looks very close!' says Isa Guha on air. Here comes Ball Tracker - PITCHING OUTSIDE LEG! Two reviews in the span of 2 balls, both favouring Pakistan in the end.
Pat Cummins to bowl from the other end.

SAFE! Masood has survived! Fuller on off and middle, Shan looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. This time all the Aussies are confident and they go up in appeal. The umpire agrees as well. Shan has a word with Imam and then signals the 'T'. Replay rolls in and Hot Spot shows a mark as it goes past the bat. There is a feather of an inside edge and Masood survives. End of a dangerous first over from Starc. Almost had an early breakthrough.

Gone! Boy, Illingworth has taken just 5 seconds to raise his finger! Masood has been adjudged LBW but he takes the review after having a long chat with Imam. Looks to be out plumb. Hold on a second, there is a bit of an inside edge which is seen on the Hot Spot. Shan survives!
On the stumps, Masood defends it off the front foot.
Another half appeal turned down. It is on the pads, Masood looks to flick but misses. The ball hits him on the pads. Starc this time is asking the question but he does not have a lot of support.

Ohh! Close call. Good length ball on off, Masood looks to defend but misses. The ball hits him high on the back pad. The fielders standing behind the stumps go up in a huge appeal but Starc does not. The umpire too is not interested. Looked too high.
Right on the money. Starc hits the deck hard and generates some extra bounce, carry and movement. Shan looks to defend but gets squared up.
Starc starts with a back of a length ball outside off. Shan leaves it alone. The ball swings as it goes past the bat.

That's all we have from this lopsided Test series. Australia will now get ready to host New Zealand while Pakistan will return home and wait for Sri Lanka. Do join us for all the action in future. Until then, it's goodbye and cheers!

Australian skipper, Tim Paine says that he is really happy and mentions that they played fantastic cricket in the last two Tests. On contributions from everyone, Paine jokingly says that not all the batsman got a chance to bat but David and Marnus were superb. Tells that Burns at the top was good too. On Warner's triple century, Paine says that it was an unbelievable knock from him. Feels that it is not easy to bat that long. On his declaration before Warner's 400 chances, Paine says that they did think that and spoke to Warner about it but David was okay with the declaration. Talking about Labuschagne, Paine says that he is enjoying his success with the bat. On the bowling, Paine says that the wicket was a difficult one and the bowlers kept coming entire time and it was an awesome performance from them. On the upcoming three-Test match series, Paine jokes that he would want to pouch a few more catches than he did. Tells that if they continue on the path they are right now, the series will be an exciting one.

Pakistan skipper, Azhar Ali starts by congratulating the Australian team and David Warner for his incredible triple hundred. Tells that it is always hard to come to Australia and beat them. Adds they have been beaten by the better side. Admits that they were poor in all three departments. Feels they need to improve their bowling and work on controlling the scoring rate. Tells that the batters need to put up big partnerships. Mentions that Yasir's fight along with Azam's knock in the first innings is a positive. Credits Babar Azam for the way he played in the series and feels that he will be a big start for Pakistan in future. Azhar hopes they can improve and learn from this tour. Ends by thanking Cricket Australia for the hospitality and the fans for their support throughout the series.

PLAYER OF THE MATCH AND SERIES, DAVID WARNER! Starts by saying that he is really happy that they didn't have to bat again. Tells that he was really tired last night and probably slept on the couch. Says that the triple hundred has not sunk in yet. Remembers his friend, late Phillip Hughes, and shares that he looked up to the skies in his memory. Tells that he is focusing on scoring runs. Adds that he backed himself and enjoyed the innings. Reminds that he was out of the game for a while but he has returned and is enjoying the game more than ever. Further says that their next series is against New Zealand and they are a quality unit. Feels that the conditions in Perth, the venue for the first Test against NZ, will suit the Kiwi attack and they will have to adjust accordingly. Finishes off by saying that he will go back and practice more in the nets and try to do his best.

Josh Hazlewood is down for a quick chat. He says that it has been a good couple of weeks for them. Mentions about Cummins' direct hit to finish things off. Reckons that it was a superb performance by the Aussie bowling unit. Praises Starc's effort in the first innings and then Lyon for his fifer. Terms it as a good all-round show. States that he is happy to start the summer in a winning way.

More than Pakistan's batting, their bowling should be faulted. Lacking in experience, there wasn't enough control shown by their young bowlers. Although Shaheen Afridi did impress by picking up three wickets. Unlike Pakistan, Australia's bowling was of top notch. Mitchell Starc wreaked havoc first time around with a 6-wicket haul and then Nathan Lyon left his impact in the final innings with a fifer. All in all, it was a completely dominant performance by Australia as they steamrolled Pakistan in the series and win it 2-0. 60 points more to their tally in the ICC World Test Championship and they are second in the list behind India.

Yet another thumping victory for Australia! Powered by Warner's magnificent triple century and Marnus Labuschagne's 162, the Kangaroos amassed 589 runs on the board. In reply, apart from Babar Azam's fluent knock and Yasir Shah's surprising century, there wasn't any fight shown by Pakistan. Tim Paine enforced the follow-on with a lead of 287 runs and once again the visiting batsmen failed to turn up with the bat. Shan Masood, Asad Shafiq and Mohammad Rizwan offered little resistance but the task in hand required a monumental effort that never came.

Right then, Australia took just under 15 minutes to pick the remaining two wickets and register yet another massive win. They are all smiles. David Warner takes a stump as a souvenir and leads his team off the park. Handshakes going on at the moment.

OUT! Wow, a direct hit by Pat Cummins to end proceedings. Very rare that you keep this guy out of action. No wickets? No problem. I shall get one through my fielding. Patto takes aim, holds his poise, stands still and fires. Bowled. Okay, run out!!! Australia's golden boy of 2019 has ended this Test match and series with a bull's eye. Fuller ball on off, Musa manages to hit it to the right of mid on. Abbas was going for a non-existent single and Musa sends him back. But Abbas is halfway down and the brilliance of Cummins finds him short. He is so short of his crease that the umpire does not even go upstairs. The Australian players are up in joy. AUSTRALIA WIN BY AN INNINGS AND 48 RUNS and they win their first series in the ICC World Test Championship.
Yes, surely, he is not going to hang around. Another length ball outside off, Musa once again looks to hammer it out of the park but this time makes no connection.

EDGY FOUR! A boundary over the slip cordon. Musa is not going to hang around. A fullish ball just outside off, Musa looks to heave but gets an outside edge which flies over the slip cordon and into the third man fence.
Targets the stumps this time and bowls it full. Musa looks to flick but makes no connection and is hit on the pads.
Beaten! Almost kisses the outside edge. Another beauty from Hazlewood. On a length and on off and middle. It once again shapes away as Musa looks to defend.
The last man in is Muhammad Musa.

OUT! Bowled 'em! No. 9 goes and the Aussies are just a wicket away from a series win. A full ball, tailing in. Rizwan looks to drive but misses and the off pole behind gets disturbed. They check for the front foot no ball but Hazlewood is fine. Third wicket for Hazlewood and Pakistan's last hope of avoiding innings defeat takes a massive dive. A fighting innings from Rizwan though.
Josh Hazlewood to operate with the second new ball from the other end.
Beaten by a beauty! It pitches around off and shapes away from the forward prod of Abbas. Lucky not to edge that one.
On a length and shaping away. Abbas has no business with it as he shoulders arms.
Bouncer, way over to trouble the batsman. Abbas ducks under it.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Good length ball shaping away and just outside off, Rizwan taps it through point for a single.
Full and on middle, Abbas pushes it towards mid off and takes a single to get off the mark.
Second new ball is available and it has been taken by Australia. Mitchell Starc will operate with it.
Down the leg side. Way down the leg side. Rizwan lets it be. The umpire lets it be too.

FOUR! Flighted ball on middle, turning back in upon landing. Rizwan skips down the track and looks to heave it over mid-wicket. At the point of contact, the ball turns in to take the inside half of his bat and Rizwan drags it over square leg for a boundary. He doesn't get the proper connection but the result is what he was looking for!
Quicker one on the pads, Rizwan stays on the back foot and taps it wide of the short leg fielder.

We are back for the final session. The Australian players walk out to the middle. Two scalps and the series will be done and dusted. Can Rizwan present some fight and force Australia to bat again? He walks out with Mohammad Abbas to resume his innings. Lyon to continue with the ball.
... Day 4, Session 3 ...

Excellent session for Australia that has fetched them three wickets and put them on the cusp of a 2-0 series win! Nathan Lyon has bounced back from the disappointment of the first innings and was once again instrumental in cutting short Pakistan's stubborn fight by claiming a fifer. 2 wickets left to pick and the only question remains is whether Rizwan rallies around with the remaining batsmen and force Australia to bat again! We will find that out soon. Do join us in a short while for what could be the final session of this Test series.

We thought that the session will be extended but Tim Paine has declined the extra 30 minutes and the Aussies are walking back for Dinner. Star of the session and this innings so far, Nathan Lyon is down for a quick chat before he heads for his break. Lyon says that it was a very good session and hopes they are clinical enough to wrap it up. On being unlucky not to get any wickets on Day 3 inspite of bowling so well, Lyon admits that is how it is. Further adds there are days you bowl badly and yet end up getting wickets.

OUT! Caught! Fifer for Lyon! What kind of shot is this, Shaheen? A tossed up ball around off, Afridi looks to launch it out of the stadium but he manages to slice it high towards mid off. The fielder, Hazlewood, settles himself and pouches the ball comfortably. 16th fifer for Lyon in Tests, 1st against Pakistan, 50th at Adelaide Oval. Two wickets remaining, will this session be extended?
Around off and turning away a hint. Afridi waits on the back foot and blocks.
Fullish and on middle, Rizwan sweeps it to fine leg for a single. 5 balls to survive for Afridi to go to Dinner.
In the channel outside off, Shaheen covers his sticks and lets it be.
Bouncer this time, on middle it is. Shaheen has no problem ducking under it.
Around off and on a fullish length. Shaheen gets his bat down in time to block it off the front foot.
Back of a length ball on middle, Rizwan pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Fuller and around off, Rizwan drives and finds the extra cover fielder.
Good length ball angling into Rizwan. He comes forward and taps it on the off side.
Tossed up on off, Shaheen taps it onto the ground and survives another over.
Floated on off, Afridi blocks it.
Around the pads, Rizwan sweeps it away for a single.
Around the pads, Rizwan looks to flick but it lobs off the inner half towards backward square leg.
Floated on off, Rizwan blocks it.
Flighted around the pads, Rizwan comes down the track and tries to flick. Lyon follows him and the ball goes towards point off his pad.
Full on off, Shaheen defends it. Well done, Shaheen. He has managed to get through the over safely.
Sprays one down the leg side. Shaheen looks to flick but misses.
Gem of a delivery. But how well has Shaheen done there? Picture perfect yorker on middle, Shaheen somehow manages to get his bat down in time to jam it out on the off side.
Going down leg. Very full. Shaheen looks to flick but the ball hits him on the front pad. The Australian players put up a huge appeal but the umpire turns it down.
Outside off, Shaheen leaves it alone.
Good length ball around off, Afridi stays back to push inside the line and then withdraws his bat at the last moment.
Mitchell Starc is back. 13-2-44-1, his figures so far.
FOUR! Terrific shot. Floated around off, Rizwan gets down on one knee and slog sweeps it over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Flighted outside off, Shaheen swings his bat at it. It goes off the outside edge towards short third man and they take a single.
Shorter on off, Afridi defends it off his back foot.
Shaheen Afridi is the new batsman. The tall man joins Rizwan and is having a word with him.

OUT! LBW! Pakistan lose one of their reviews. The centurion from the first innings cannot hang around for long this time around. Shorter and slightly quicker on off. It pitches and straightens. Yasir looks to play from the back foot but is late on it and the ball hits him flush on the pads. The Aussies appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Yasir makes eye-contact with Rizwan and then signals the 'T'. Replays roll in.  First Hot Spot shows that there is no involvement of the bat. Snicko confirms it later on. Ball Tracker then comes in and it reflects all reds. Yasir has to walk back. No heroics from him in the second innings. Pakistan still trail by 66 runs.

Big shout for an lbw! FINGER GOES UP! Yasir Shah has a clueless look on his face and then decides to take the DRS. Is it too high? There is no bat on the Hot Spot and Snicko. Here comes the Ball Tracker...and it's hitting the top of off stump. No heroics in this innings from Yasir Shah.
Slightly shorter on middle, Yasir taps it back to the bowler.
Flighted leg spinner on middle, Yasir looks to flick but it goes off his pad and falls in front of short leg.
End of an over where none of the balls were pitched up. It is around off, Rizwan sways away from it.
Bouncer to Rizwan now. He gets under it.
Back of a length on off, Yasir glances it towards fine leg for one.
Hat-trick of short balls. This time Shah ducks under it.
Another short ball. This is down the leg side. Yasir looks to pull but it goes off his gloves fine down the leg side. They take two.
Back of a length on off, Yasir glances it towards square leg.
Flights one on off, Rizwan strokes it to point.
Shorter on off, Rizwan defends it off the back foot.
Floated on the stumps, Yasir glances it towards mid-wicket for one.
Flighted around off, Yasir strokes it through covers for a couple.
Shorter on off, Rizwan whips it towards square leg for a single.
Floated on middle, Rizwan strokes it back to the bowler.

Slight halt in play! Physio is out performing the concussion check on Marnus Labuschagne. That ball has hit him flush on top of the helmet. The young man is smiling and appears to be fine. No change of helmet, Marnus is just fixing the existing one.

Oohhh... That's struck Labuschagne on the helmet and the short leg fielder nearly assisted a catch. Back of a length ball on off, Rizwan gets back and pulls it firmly across the line. Labuschagne at short leg is quick to duck. The ball hits him on his helmet and lobs wide of mid on. The fielder there cannot get around quickly and they take a single. Labuschagne is unaware where the ball is. Rizwan after completing the run goes to apologize to Marnus. He smiles and indicates everything is okay!
This time flicks it towards mid-wicket for a run.

FOUR! Yasir continues from where he left of in the first innings. Fuller on middle and leg, Yasir flicks it away over backward square leg for a boundary. It looked similar to Kevin Pietersen's flamingo flick. This is what form does to a batsman (errr bowler).
Bouncer! Just around off. Yasir initially looks to play but then sways away from it. Nicely done as he never took his eyes off the ball.
